WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:07.074


00:48.300 --> 00:50.065
ROGERS: On your left.

01:00.380 --> 01:01.699
On your left.

01:01.700 --> 01:04.148
MAN: Uh-huh. On my left. Got it.

01:09.500 --> 01:10.939
Don't say it. Don't you say it.

01:10.940 --> 01:12.910
- On your left.
- Come on!

01:13.500 --> 01:15.419
(PANTING) Oh!

01:15.420 --> 01:18.107
(GROANING)

01:21.340 --> 01:23.019
Need a medic?

01:23.020 --> 01:24.467
(LAUGHS)

01:25.620 --> 01:27.419
I need a new set of lungs.

01:27.420 --> 01:30.859
Dude, you just ran, like,
13 miles in 30 minutes.

01:30.860 --> 01:32.099
I guess I got a late start.

01:32.100 --> 01:34.819
(CHUCKLES) Really? You should
be ashamed of yourself.

01:34.820 --> 01:37.459
You should take another lap.

01:37.460 --> 01:39.908
Did you just take it?
I assume you just took it.

01:39.980 --> 01:41.459
What unit you with?

01:41.460 --> 01:43.019
58th Pararescue.

01:43.020 --> 01:44.945
But now I'm working down at the VA.

01:45.260 --> 01:47.019
- Sam Wilson.
- Steve Rogers.

01:47.020 --> 01:49.582
I kind of put that together.
(PANTING)

01:50.300 --> 01:52.939
Must have freaked you out, coming home
after the whole defrosting thing.

01:52.940 --> 01:55.539
(SIGHS)
It takes some getting used to.

01:55.540 --> 01:57.351
It's good to meet you, Sam.

01:57.380 --> 01:58.781
It's your bed, right?

01:59.620 --> 02:00.699
What's that?

02:00.700 --> 02:02.379
Your bed, it's too soft.

02:02.380 --> 02:04.179
When I was over there,
I'd sleep on the ground,

02:04.180 --> 02:06.379
use rock for pillows,
like a caveman.

02:06.380 --> 02:09.499
Now I'm home, lying in
my bed, and it's like...

02:09.500 --> 02:10.859
Lying on a marshmallow.

02:10.860 --> 02:12.910
Feel like I'm gonna sink
right to the floor.

02:13.900 --> 02:15.219
How long?

02:15.220 --> 02:16.906
Two tours.

02:17.540 --> 02:19.385
You must miss the
good old days, huh?

02:19.940 --> 02:22.619
Well, things aren't so bad.

02:22.620 --> 02:25.059
Food's a lot better. We
used to boil everything.

02:25.060 --> 02:26.419
No polio is good.

02:26.420 --> 02:27.899
Internet, so helpful.

02:27.900 --> 02:29.820
I've been reading that a
lot, trying to catch up.

02:31.460 --> 02:35.619
Marvin Gaye, 1972,
<i>Trouble Man</i> soundtrack.

02:35.620 --> 02:38.259
Everything you missed
jammed into one album.

02:38.260 --> 02:40.628
I'll put it on the list.

02:44.260 --> 02:46.549
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

02:47.860 --> 02:50.779
All right, Sam, duty calls.
Thanks for the run.

02:50.780 --> 02:52.299
If that's what you
want to call running.

02:52.300 --> 02:53.379
Oh, that's how it is?

02:53.380 --> 02:54.941
- Oh, that's how it is.
- Okay. (LAUGHS)

02:56.100 --> 02:58.579
Any time you want to stop by
the VA, make me look awesome

02:58.580 --> 03:02.099
in front of the girl at the
front desk, just let me know.

03:02.100 --> 03:04.150
- I'll keep it in mind.
- Yeah.

03:07.740 --> 03:09.499
Hey, fellas.

03:09.500 --> 03:11.459
Either one of you know
where the Smithsonian is?

03:11.460 --> 03:13.066
I'm here to pick up a fossil.

03:13.100 --> 03:14.501
ROGERS: That's hilarious.

03:17.580 --> 03:18.659
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

03:18.660 --> 03:20.505
- How you doing?
- Hey.

03:21.580 --> 03:22.939
Can't run everywhere.

03:22.940 --> 03:24.341
No, you can't.

03:25.700 --> 03:27.625
(TYRES SCREECHING)

03:31.780 --> 03:34.019
Target is a mobile
satellite launch platform,

03:34.020 --> 03:35.459
the <i>Lemurian Star.</i>

03:35.460 --> 03:37.988
They were sending up their last
payload when pirates took them,

03:38.220 --> 03:39.739
93 minutes ago.

03:39.740 --> 03:41.619
- Any demands?
- Billion and a half.

03:41.620 --> 03:43.740
- ROGERS: Why so steep?
- Because it's S.H.I.E.L.D.'s.

03:45.820 --> 03:47.659
So it's not off-course.
It's trespassing.

03:47.660 --> 03:49.299
I'm sure they have a good reason.

03:49.300 --> 03:51.219
You know, I'm getting a little
tired of being Fury's janitor.

03:51.220 --> 03:53.259
Relax. It's not that complicated.

03:53.260 --> 03:54.459
How many pirates?

03:54.460 --> 03:57.386
25. Top mercs led by this guy.

03:57.780 --> 04:01.459
Georges Batroc. Ex-DGSE,
Action Division.

04:01.460 --> 04:03.749
He's at the top of
Interpol's Red Notice.

04:03.980 --> 04:07.419
Before the French demobilised
him, he had 36 kill missions.

04:07.420 --> 04:09.219
This guy's got a rep for
maximum casualties.

04:09.220 --> 04:10.539
Hostages?

04:10.540 --> 04:13.830
Oh, mostly techs.
One officer. Jasper Sitwell.

04:14.100 --> 04:15.499
They're in the galley.

04:15.500 --> 04:17.179
What's Sitwell doing
on a launch ship?

04:17.180 --> 04:19.219
All right, I'm gonna sweep
the deck and find Batroc.

04:19.220 --> 04:21.065
Nat, you kill the engines
and wait for instructions.

04:21.180 --> 04:23.859
Rumlow, you sweep aft,
find the hostages,

04:23.860 --> 04:25.739
get them to the life-pods,
get them out. Let's move.

04:25.740 --> 04:27.341
S.T.R.I.K.E., you heard
the Cap. Gear up.

04:40.980 --> 04:42.139
Secure channel seven.

04:42.140 --> 04:43.379
Seven secure.

04:43.380 --> 04:45.179
Did you do anything
fun Saturday night?

04:45.180 --> 04:48.699
Well, all the guys from my
barbershop quartet are dead,

04:48.700 --> 04:50.339
so, no, not really.

04:50.340 --> 04:52.739
<i>MALE PILOT ON RADIO:
Coming up on the drop zone, Cap.</i>

04:52.740 --> 04:56.144
You know, if you ask Kristen out, from
Statistics, she'd probably say yes.

04:56.660 --> 04:58.027
That's why I don't ask.

04:59.540 --> 05:01.544
Too shy, or too scared?

05:01.940 --> 05:03.671
Too busy!

05:04.740 --> 05:06.499
Was he wearing a parachute?

05:06.500 --> 05:07.947
No.

05:08.180 --> 05:09.627
No, he wasn't.

06:10.260 --> 06:11.866
Ahh!

06:18.060 --> 06:19.219
Ahh!

06:19.220 --> 06:20.860
(SPLASHES)

06:21.980 --> 06:23.541
(BOTH GRUNTING)

06:23.660 --> 06:25.061
Hey!

06:31.140 --> 06:32.826
(SCREAMS)

06:43.500 --> 06:45.061
(GRUNTING)

07:02.460 --> 07:03.539
- (COCKS GUN)
- (SPEAKS FRENCH)

07:03.540 --> 07:04.941
Don't move.

07:08.740 --> 07:09.979
Thanks.

07:09.980 --> 07:12.382
Yeah. You seemed pretty
helpless without me.

07:16.660 --> 07:18.379
What about the nurse that lives
across the hall from you?

07:18.380 --> 07:19.539
She seems kind of nice.

07:19.540 --> 07:21.339
Secure the engine room,
then find me a date.

07:21.340 --> 07:23.019
I'm multi-tasking.

07:23.020 --> 07:24.339
(FRENCH PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

07:24.340 --> 07:25.739
<i>I told Batroc...</i>

07:25.740 --> 07:27.219
If we want to make
S.H.I.E.L.D. pay us...

07:27.220 --> 07:29.702
start sending them bodies now!

07:31.180 --> 07:33.628
I have a bullet for someone...

07:34.020 --> 07:35.819
You want a bullet in your head?

07:35.820 --> 07:37.790
Move that foot - you want
a bullet in the head...?

07:38.060 --> 07:39.791
Huh?

07:45.700 --> 07:47.379
(BATROC SPEAKING FRENCH)

07:47.380 --> 07:49.623
I don't like waiting.

07:50.340 --> 07:51.901
Call Durand.

07:52.180 --> 07:54.899
I want this ship ready to
move when the ransom comes.

07:54.900 --> 07:56.870
(RADIO PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

08:02.580 --> 08:03.899
Start the engines.

08:03.900 --> 08:05.381
Okay.

08:06.260 --> 08:07.741
Hey, sailor.

08:09.300 --> 08:10.826
(SCREAMS)

08:12.260 --> 08:13.707
(CHOKING)

08:25.260 --> 08:27.139
(PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

08:27.140 --> 08:28.541
Shut up.

08:29.460 --> 08:32.181
You want to be a hero? Is that it?

08:38.260 --> 08:40.867
All right, I've
waited long enough...

08:43.780 --> 08:45.139
Hey!

08:45.140 --> 08:46.219
Find Batroc...

08:46.220 --> 08:47.419
IF I don't hear anything
in two minutes...

08:47.420 --> 08:48.779
I start killing them!

08:48.780 --> 08:50.181
I'll Find him.

08:58.820 --> 09:00.142
Two minutes.

09:31.140 --> 09:33.907
Radio silence from
S.H.I.E.L.D., Batroc...

09:37.860 --> 09:39.307
Targets acquired.

09:39.620 --> 09:41.067
S.T.R.I.K.E. in position.

09:41.780 --> 09:43.227
Natasha, what's your status?

09:45.500 --> 09:46.659
<i>Status, Natasha.</i>

09:46.660 --> 09:48.061
Hang on!

09:52.020 --> 09:53.581
(GROANING)

10:03.740 --> 10:05.266
Engine room secure.

10:12.420 --> 10:13.579
(PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

10:13.580 --> 10:14.981
Time is up.

10:15.980 --> 10:17.984
Who dies first...?

10:19.020 --> 10:20.139
You!

10:20.140 --> 10:21.541
Get that one.

10:23.700 --> 10:25.101
On my mark.

10:26.180 --> 10:27.699
<i>Three...</i>

10:27.700 --> 10:29.219
<i>Two... One.</i>

10:29.220 --> 10:31.031
- (GUNFIRE)
- (PIRATES GASP)

10:35.340 --> 10:38.789
I told you, S.H.I.E.L.D.
doesn't negotiate.

10:38.820 --> 10:40.790
(RADIO PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

10:42.060 --> 10:43.819
The line just went dead.

10:43.820 --> 10:45.631
I've lost contact with them...

10:47.340 --> 10:48.980
Ahh!

10:58.780 --> 11:01.308
Hostages en route to extraction.

11:01.780 --> 11:04.626
<i>Romanoff missed the
rendezvous point, Cap.</i>

11:04.780 --> 11:06.899
<i>Hostiles are still in play.</i>

11:06.900 --> 11:09.459
(PANTING)
Natasha, Batroc's on the move.

11:09.460 --> 11:11.908
Circle back to Rumlow and
protect the hostages.

11:12.420 --> 11:13.946
Natasha.

11:15.180 --> 11:16.786
(BOTH GRUNTING)

11:48.620 --> 11:50.099
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

11:50.100 --> 11:52.104
I thought you were more
than just a shield...

12:05.980 --> 12:07.870
Let's see.

12:32.100 --> 12:33.259
(PANTING)

12:33.260 --> 12:35.185
ROMANOFF: Well, this is awkward.

12:38.220 --> 12:39.579
What are you doing?

12:39.580 --> 12:40.899
Backing up the hard drive.

12:40.900 --> 12:42.711
It's a good habit to get into.

12:42.820 --> 12:43.979
Rumlow needed your help.

12:43.980 --> 12:45.666
What the hell are you doing here?

12:48.860 --> 12:50.179
You're saving S.H.I.E.L.D. intel.

12:50.180 --> 12:51.659
Whatever I can get my hands on.

12:51.660 --> 12:53.139
Our mission is to rescue hostages.

12:53.140 --> 12:55.383
No, that's your mission,

12:56.820 --> 12:58.187
and you've done it beautifully.

12:58.980 --> 13:00.939
You just jeopardised
this whole operation.

13:00.940 --> 13:02.705
I think that's overstating things.

13:14.500 --> 13:16.231
(BOTH GROANING)

13:17.380 --> 13:19.305
(BOTH PANTING)

13:20.300 --> 13:21.826
Okay.

13:22.140 --> 13:23.746
That one's on me.

13:24.380 --> 13:26.145
You're damn right.

13:29.020 --> 13:30.626
(SIGHS)

13:54.620 --> 13:56.739
ROGERS: You just can't stop
yourself from lying, can you?

13:56.740 --> 13:57.859
FURY: I didn't lie.

13:57.860 --> 13:59.419
Agent Romanoff had a different
mission than yours.

13:59.420 --> 14:01.379
Which you didn't feel
obliged to share.

14:01.380 --> 14:03.099
I'm not obliged to do anything.

14:03.100 --> 14:04.739
Those hostages could
have died, Nick.

14:04.740 --> 14:08.499
I sent the greatest soldier in history
to make sure that didn't happen.

14:08.500 --> 14:10.819
Soldiers trust each other.
That's what makes it an army.

14:10.820 --> 14:12.619
Not a bunch of guys running
around shooting guns.

14:12.620 --> 14:16.229
Last time I trusted
someone, I lost an eye.

14:16.820 --> 14:20.379
Look, I didn't want you doing anything
you weren't comfortable with.

14:20.380 --> 14:22.699
Agent Romanoff is comfortable
with everything.

14:22.700 --> 14:24.059
I can't lead a mission

14:24.060 --> 14:25.979
when the people I'm leading
have missions of their own.

14:25.980 --> 14:28.819
It's called compartmentalisation.

14:28.820 --> 14:31.905
Nobody spills the secrets,
because nobody knows them all.

14:32.460 --> 14:33.827
Except you.

14:37.140 --> 14:39.065
You're wrong about me.

14:39.500 --> 14:41.140
I do share.

14:41.940 --> 14:43.910
I'm nice like that.

14:45.420 --> 14:46.539
Insight bay.

14:46.540 --> 14:47.859
<i>S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
Captain Rogers does not have</i>

14:47.860 --> 14:49.219
<i>clearance for Project Insight.</i>

14:49.220 --> 14:51.819
Director override.
Fury, Nicholas J.

14:51.820 --> 14:53.790
<i>- Confirmed.</i>
- (DOOR CLOSES)

14:55.980 --> 14:58.223
You know, they used to play music.

14:58.500 --> 14:59.659
Yeah.

14:59.660 --> 15:03.459
My grandfather operated one
of these things for 40 years.

15:03.460 --> 15:05.939
Granddad worked in a nice building.

15:05.940 --> 15:07.546
Got good tips.

15:07.740 --> 15:12.019
He'd walk home every night, a roll
of ones stuffed in his lunch bag.

15:12.020 --> 15:13.579
He'd say, "Hi."

15:13.580 --> 15:15.823
People would say, "Hi" back.

15:16.180 --> 15:18.699
Time went on, the
neighbourhood got rougher.

15:18.700 --> 15:20.101
He'd say, "Hi."

15:20.380 --> 15:22.459
They'd say, "Keep on steppin'."

15:22.460 --> 15:24.942
Granddad got to gripping that
lunch bag a little tighter.

15:25.500 --> 15:26.859
Did he ever get mugged?

15:26.860 --> 15:28.466
(LAUGHS)

15:28.620 --> 15:31.699
Every week some punk would
say, "What's in the bag?"

15:31.700 --> 15:33.539
What would he do?

15:33.540 --> 15:35.101
He'd show them.

15:35.340 --> 15:39.142
Bunch of crumpled ones,
and a loaded .22 Magnum.

15:42.900 --> 15:44.984
Yeah, Granddad loved people.

15:45.540 --> 15:48.227
But he didn't trust them very much.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.539
Yeah, I know.

15:55.540 --> 15:58.261
They're a little bit
bigger than a .22.

16:32.220 --> 16:34.819
FURY: This is Project Insight.

16:34.820 --> 16:37.219
Three next-generation helicarriers

16:37.220 --> 16:40.099
synced to a network of
targeting satellites.

16:40.100 --> 16:42.059
Launched from the <i>Lemurian Star</i>.

16:42.060 --> 16:45.259
Once we get them in the air,
they never need to come down.

16:45.260 --> 16:50.299
Continuous sub-orbital flight,
courtesy of our new repulsor engines.

16:50.300 --> 16:51.659
Stark?

16:51.660 --> 16:52.979
He had a few suggestions

16:52.980 --> 16:55.701
once he got an up-close
look at our old turbines.

16:56.180 --> 16:58.779
These new long-range precision guns

16:58.780 --> 17:01.419
can eliminate 1,000
hostiles a minute.

17:01.420 --> 17:06.030
The satellites can read a terrorist's DNA
before he steps outside his spider hole.

17:06.100 --> 17:09.099
We're gonna neutralise a lot of
threats before they even happen.

17:09.100 --> 17:11.179
Thought the punishment usually
came after the crime.

17:11.180 --> 17:12.779
We can't afford to wait that long.

17:12.780 --> 17:14.499
Who's "we"?

17:14.500 --> 17:16.939
After New York, I convinced
the World Security Council

17:16.940 --> 17:19.627
we needed a quantum surge
in threat analysis.

17:20.100 --> 17:22.707
For once, we're way
ahead of the curve.

17:23.060 --> 17:26.384
By holding a gun to everyone on
Earth and calling it protection.

17:27.580 --> 17:30.028
You know, I read those SSR files.

17:30.420 --> 17:31.901
"Greatest Generation"?

17:32.260 --> 17:34.099
You guys did some nasty stuff.

17:34.100 --> 17:36.025
Yeah, we compromised.

17:36.140 --> 17:38.383
Sometimes in ways that
made us not sleep so well.

17:38.460 --> 17:40.939
But we did it so that
people could be free.

17:40.940 --> 17:43.299
This isn't freedom. This is fear.

17:43.300 --> 17:46.899
S.H.I.E.L.D. takes the world as
it is, not as we'd like it to be.

17:46.900 --> 17:51.271
And it's getting damn near past time for
you to get with that programme, Cap.

17:51.860 --> 17:54.103
Don't hold your breath.

18:12.380 --> 18:14.499
<i>WOMAN ON PA:
Welcome to the Smithsonian.</i>

18:14.500 --> 18:18.427
<i>Visitor information booths are
available on the second level.</i>

18:27.060 --> 18:29.588
<i>NARRATOR: A symbol to the nation.</i>

18:30.380 --> 18:32.544
<i>A hero to the world.</i>

18:33.540 --> 18:39.788
<i>The story of Captain America is one
of honour, bravery and sacrifice.</i>

18:44.060 --> 18:47.059
<i>Denied enlistment
due to poor health,</i>

18:47.060 --> 18:49.459
<i>Steven Rogers was
chosen for a programme</i>

18:49.460 --> 18:52.989
<i>unique in the annals
of American warfare.</i>

18:53.580 --> 18:58.941
<i>One that would transform him into
the world's first Super-Soldier.</i>

19:05.220 --> 19:06.379
<i>WAR FOOTAGE NARRATOR:
In this rare footage,</i>

19:06.380 --> 19:08.899
<i>everyone's favourite war
hero, Captain America...</i>

19:08.900 --> 19:10.579
<i>NARRATOR: Battle tested,</i>

19:10.580 --> 19:11.939
<i>Captain America</i>

19:11.940 --> 19:15.219
<i>and his Howling Commandos
quickly earned their stripes.</i>

19:15.220 --> 19:16.659
<i>Their mission:</i>

19:16.660 --> 19:20.701
<i>taking down HYDRA, the Nazi
rogue science division.</i>

19:23.620 --> 19:26.022
<i>Best friends since childhood,</i>

19:26.580 --> 19:30.099
<i>Bucky Barnes and Steven
Rogers were inseparable</i>

19:30.100 --> 19:32.389
<i>on both schoolyard and battlefield.</i>

19:33.380 --> 19:37.579
<i>Barnes is the only Howling
Commando to give his life</i>

19:37.580 --> 19:40.551
<i>in service of his country.</i>

19:45.220 --> 19:47.019
<i>PEGGY ON VIDEO:
That was a difficult winter.</i>

19:47.020 --> 19:50.902
<i>A blizzard had trapped half our
battalion behind the German line.</i>

19:51.260 --> 19:54.539
<i>Steve, Captain Rogers,</i>

19:54.540 --> 19:57.379
<i>he fought his way through
a HYDRA blockade</i>

19:57.380 --> 20:00.306
<i>that had pinned our
allies down for months.</i>

20:01.860 --> 20:03.705
<i>He saved over 1,000 men.</i>

20:04.300 --> 20:06.270
<i>Including the man who would...</i>

20:07.180 --> 20:10.550
<i>Who would become my
husband, as it turned out.</i>

20:11.020 --> 20:14.185
<i>Even after he died, Steve
was still changing my life.</i>

20:16.820 --> 20:18.710
You should be proud
of yourself, Peggy.

20:24.340 --> 20:26.105
Mmm.

20:26.700 --> 20:29.228
I have lived a life.

20:30.740 --> 20:34.349
My only regret is that you
didn't get to live yours.

20:37.140 --> 20:38.587
What is it?

20:41.140 --> 20:44.828
For as long as I can remember,
I just wanted to do what was right.

20:45.860 --> 20:48.581
I guess I'm not quite sure
what that is any more.

20:51.060 --> 20:55.499
And I thought I could throw
myself back in and follow orders.

20:55.500 --> 20:57.390
Serve.

21:00.140 --> 21:02.539
It's just not the same.

21:02.540 --> 21:04.624
(LAUGHS) You're always so dramatic.

21:07.460 --> 21:11.467
Look, you saved the world.

21:13.540 --> 21:17.739
We rather mucked it up.

21:17.740 --> 21:19.426
You didn't.

21:19.580 --> 21:23.701
Knowing that you helped found
S.H.I.E.L.D. is half the reason I stay.

21:24.140 --> 21:25.587
Hey.

21:28.020 --> 21:32.664
The world has changed,
and none of us can go back.

21:33.460 --> 21:35.819
All we can do is our best.

21:35.820 --> 21:40.179
And sometimes the best that
we can do is to start over.

21:40.180 --> 21:42.105
(COUGHING)

21:47.540 --> 21:48.941
Peggy.

21:54.380 --> 21:55.781
Steve.

21:56.220 --> 21:57.667
Yeah?

21:57.860 --> 21:58.939
(GASPS)

21:58.940 --> 22:00.626
You're alive.

22:01.220 --> 22:04.259
You came back.

22:04.260 --> 22:05.661
Yeah, Peggy.

22:08.780 --> 22:11.421
It's been so long.

22:13.580 --> 22:15.470
So long.

22:16.100 --> 22:18.819
Well, I couldn't
leave my best girl.

22:18.820 --> 22:21.348
Not when she owes me a dance.

22:26.940 --> 22:28.705
Secure office.

22:36.220 --> 22:39.510
Open <i>Lemurian Star's</i>
satellite launch file.

22:40.140 --> 22:42.269
<i>S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
Access denied.</i>

22:42.580 --> 22:43.981
Run decryption.

22:46.180 --> 22:48.299
<i>Decryption failed.</i>

22:48.300 --> 22:51.385
Director override.
Fury, Nicholas J.

22:53.020 --> 22:56.259
<i>Override denied. All files sealed.</i>

22:56.260 --> 22:57.899
On whose authority?

22:57.900 --> 23:00.541
<i>Fury, Nicholas J.</i>

23:05.700 --> 23:06.979
World Security Council.

23:06.980 --> 23:08.586
<i>Confirmed.</i>

23:10.820 --> 23:13.299
<i>ROCKWELL: If Nick Fury thinks
he can get his costumed thugs</i>

23:13.300 --> 23:16.739
<i>and S.T.R.I.K.E. commandos to mop
up his mess, he's sadly mistaken.</i>

23:16.740 --> 23:18.099
This failure is unacceptable.

23:18.100 --> 23:19.899
Considering this attack took place

23:19.900 --> 23:21.819
one mile from my country's
sovereign waters,

23:21.820 --> 23:24.459
it's a bit more than that.
I move for immediate hearing.

23:24.460 --> 23:26.499
We don't need hearings,
we need action.

23:26.500 --> 23:28.899
It's this Council's duty
to oversee S.H.I.E.L.D.

23:28.900 --> 23:30.979
A breach like this raises
serious questions.

23:30.980 --> 23:32.859
Like how the hell
did a French pirate

23:32.860 --> 23:36.939
manage to hijack a covert S.H.I.E.L.D.
vessel in broad daylight?

23:36.940 --> 23:39.422
For the record, Councilman,
he's Algerian.

23:39.660 --> 23:41.819
I can draw a map if it'd help.

23:41.820 --> 23:45.064
I appreciate your wit,
Secretary Pierce.

23:45.500 --> 23:48.659
But this Council takes things like
international piracy fairly seriously.

23:48.660 --> 23:52.269
Really? I don't.

23:53.300 --> 23:56.271
I don't care about one boat,
I care about the fleet.

23:56.980 --> 23:59.859
If this Council is going
to fall to rancour

23:59.860 --> 24:02.945
every time someone pushes
us on the playing field,

24:03.780 --> 24:06.019
maybe we need someone
to oversee us.

24:06.020 --> 24:08.946
YEN: Mr Secretary,
nobody is suggesting...

24:12.620 --> 24:13.739
Excuse me.

24:13.740 --> 24:15.539
More trouble, Mr Secretary?

24:15.540 --> 24:17.544
PIERCE: Depends on your definition.

24:20.420 --> 24:22.310
(DOOR OPENING)

24:25.900 --> 24:29.179
I work 40 floors away and it takes
a hijacking for you to visit?

24:29.180 --> 24:31.662
A nuclear war would do it, too.

24:32.420 --> 24:33.899
You busy in there?

24:33.900 --> 24:35.790
Nothing some earmarks can't fix.

24:37.380 --> 24:41.102
I'm here to ask a favour.

24:41.500 --> 24:43.579
I want you to call for a vote.

24:43.580 --> 24:46.059
Project Insight has to be delayed.

24:46.060 --> 24:48.459
Nick, that's not a favour,

24:48.460 --> 24:50.139
that's a sub-committee
hearing. A long one.

24:50.140 --> 24:51.979
It could be nothing.
It probably is nothing.

24:51.980 --> 24:54.819
I just need time to
make sure it's nothing.

24:54.820 --> 24:56.059
But if it's something?

24:56.060 --> 24:59.270
Then we'll both be damn glad those
helicarriers aren't in the air.

25:01.020 --> 25:02.342
Fine.

25:02.700 --> 25:06.627
But you got to get Iron Man to
stop by my niece's birthday party.

25:06.700 --> 25:08.219
Thank you, sir.

25:08.220 --> 25:11.510
And not just a flyby.
He's got to mingle.

25:13.780 --> 25:15.341
<i>GARCIA: The thing is,</i>

25:15.540 --> 25:17.908
I think it's getting worse.

25:18.780 --> 25:21.259
A cop pulled me over last week.

25:21.260 --> 25:22.946
He thought I was drunk.

25:23.700 --> 25:27.582
I swerved to miss a plastic bag.

25:28.620 --> 25:30.829
I thought it was an IED.

25:32.700 --> 25:34.899
WILSON: Some stuff you leave there.

25:34.900 --> 25:37.139
Other stuff you bring back.

25:37.140 --> 25:40.259
It's our job to figure
out how to carry it.

25:40.260 --> 25:44.824
Is it gonna be in a big suitcase,
or in a little man-purse?

25:45.580 --> 25:47.027
It's up to you.

25:47.820 --> 25:49.585
- I'll see you next week.
- Definitely.

25:51.220 --> 25:53.907
Look who it is, the running man.

25:54.380 --> 25:57.019
Caught the last few minutes.
It's pretty intense.

25:57.020 --> 26:00.390
Yeah, brother, we all
got the same problems.

26:00.700 --> 26:02.306
Guilt,

26:02.340 --> 26:03.980
regret.

26:04.140 --> 26:06.110
You lose someone?

26:06.340 --> 26:09.141
My wingman, Riley.

26:09.740 --> 26:10.979
Flying a night mission.

26:10.980 --> 26:13.539
Standard PJ rescue op.

26:13.540 --> 26:15.779
Nothing we hadn't done
1,000 times before.

26:15.780 --> 26:19.787
Until an RPG knocked Riley's
dumb ass out of the sky.

26:21.500 --> 26:23.231
Nothing I could do.

26:23.420 --> 26:25.822
It's like I was up
there just to watch.

26:26.540 --> 26:28.659
- I'm sorry.
- After that,

26:28.660 --> 26:32.701
I had a really hard time finding a
reason for being over there, you know?

26:34.260 --> 26:36.901
But you're happy now,
back in the world?

26:37.340 --> 26:41.179
The number of people giving me
orders is down to about zero.

26:41.180 --> 26:42.581
So, hell yeah.

26:43.300 --> 26:44.747
Are you thinking about getting out?

26:45.340 --> 26:46.741
No.

26:48.380 --> 26:49.941
I don't know.

26:51.060 --> 26:54.031
To be honest, I don't know what I
would do with myself if I did.

26:54.140 --> 26:55.541
- Ultimate fighting?
- (LAUGHS)

26:55.980 --> 26:58.539
Just a great idea off
the top of my head.

26:58.540 --> 27:01.341
Seriously, you could do
whatever you want to do.

27:01.940 --> 27:03.387
What makes you happy?

27:04.900 --> 27:06.984
I don't know.

27:08.060 --> 27:11.059
<i>ELECTRONIC VOICE: Activating
communications encryption protocol.</i>

27:11.060 --> 27:13.747
Open secure line 0405.

27:13.820 --> 27:15.267
<i>Confirmed.</i>

27:16.220 --> 27:17.419
<i>This is Hill.</i>

27:17.420 --> 27:19.459
I need you here in D.C.

27:19.460 --> 27:22.591
Deep shadow conditions.

27:22.860 --> 27:24.099
<i>Give me four hours.</i>

27:24.100 --> 27:26.104
You have three. Over.

27:41.940 --> 27:44.024
Want to see my lease?

27:45.100 --> 27:47.150
(SIREN WAILS)

28:01.540 --> 28:02.899
<i>ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Fracture detected.</i>

28:02.900 --> 28:04.301
(GASPING)

28:05.940 --> 28:08.707
<i>Recommend anaesthetic injection.</i>

28:13.060 --> 28:16.782
<i>D.C. Metro Police dispatch
shows no units in this area.</i>

28:21.660 --> 28:23.107
Get me out of here.

28:25.460 --> 28:26.819
<i>Propulsion systems offline.</i>

28:26.820 --> 28:28.221
Then reboot, damn it!

28:48.580 --> 28:50.339
<i>Warning. Window
integrity compromised.</i>

28:50.340 --> 28:52.310
You think?

28:52.740 --> 28:54.983
(DRILLING)

28:55.340 --> 28:56.459
How long to propulsion?

28:56.460 --> 28:57.861
<i>Calculating.</i>

29:00.700 --> 29:03.979
<i>Window integrity 31%.
Deploying countermeasures.</i>

29:03.980 --> 29:05.506
Hold that order!

29:06.900 --> 29:09.179
<i>Window integrity 19%.</i>

29:09.180 --> 29:10.299
<i>Offensive measures advised.</i>

29:10.300 --> 29:12.031
Wait!

29:14.860 --> 29:16.819
<i>Window integrity 1%.</i>

29:16.820 --> 29:18.381
Now!

29:28.380 --> 29:30.179
<i>Propulsion systems now online.</i>

29:30.180 --> 29:31.539
Full acceleration! Now!

29:31.540 --> 29:33.544
(ENGINE REVVING)

29:47.420 --> 29:48.939
Initiate vertical takeoff!

29:48.940 --> 29:50.019
<i>Flight systems damaged.</i>

29:50.020 --> 29:52.388
Then activate guidance cameras!

29:53.220 --> 29:54.621
(GROANING)

29:55.380 --> 29:56.781
Give me the wheel!

30:04.140 --> 30:05.459
Get me Agent Hill.

30:05.460 --> 30:07.100
<i>Communications array damaged.</i>

30:07.340 --> 30:08.579
Well, what's not damaged?

30:08.580 --> 30:11.142
<i>Air conditioning is
fully operational.</i>

30:22.540 --> 30:23.739
<i>Traffic ahead.</i>

30:23.740 --> 30:24.779
Give me an alternate route.

30:24.780 --> 30:26.739
<i>Traffic alert on Roosevelt Bridge.</i>

30:26.740 --> 30:28.179
<i>All vehicles stopped.</i>

30:28.180 --> 30:31.982
<i>17th Avenue clear in three
blocks, directly ahead.</i>

30:34.420 --> 30:36.265
(TYRES SCREECHING)

30:47.420 --> 30:48.901
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

31:13.140 --> 31:14.541
(GROANS)

31:33.500 --> 31:35.664
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

32:08.020 --> 32:09.626
<i>Warning. Approaching intersection.</i>

32:18.100 --> 32:20.579
Get me off the grid!

32:20.580 --> 32:22.664
<i>Calculating route
to secure location.</i>

33:36.700 --> 33:40.343
So sweet. That is so nice.

33:40.900 --> 33:42.179
Hi.

33:42.180 --> 33:43.741
I got to go, though.

33:44.140 --> 33:45.746
Okay. Bye.

33:46.540 --> 33:48.544
My aunt, she's kind
of an insomniac.

33:49.900 --> 33:51.301
Yeah.

33:52.540 --> 33:53.779
Hey, if you want...

33:53.780 --> 33:56.179
If you want, you're welcome
to use my machine.

33:56.180 --> 33:58.105
Might be cheaper than the
one in the basement.

33:58.620 --> 34:00.431
Oh, yeah? What's it cost?

34:00.980 --> 34:03.109
A cup of coffee?

34:05.740 --> 34:07.551
Thank you, but

34:07.700 --> 34:09.579
I already have a
load in downstairs,

34:09.580 --> 34:12.619
and you really don't want
my scrubs in your machine.

34:12.620 --> 34:15.859
I just finished a rotation in the
infectious disease ward, so...

34:15.860 --> 34:18.019
Well, I'll keep my distance.

34:18.020 --> 34:19.546
Hopefully, not too far.

34:20.020 --> 34:22.259
(1940s MUSIC PLAYING
IN THE DISTANCE)

34:22.260 --> 34:24.105
Oh, and I think you
left your stereo on.

34:24.220 --> 34:25.299
Oh.

34:25.300 --> 34:26.979
Right. Thank you.

34:26.980 --> 34:28.381
Yeah.

34:31.220 --> 34:33.509
(1940s MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING)

34:47.500 --> 34:49.902
(MUSIC STOPS)

34:52.260 --> 34:55.982
(1940s MUSIC RESUMES PLAYING)

35:13.780 --> 35:15.779
I don't remember giving you a key.

35:15.780 --> 35:17.459
(GRUNTS)

35:17.460 --> 35:19.942
You really think I'd need one?

35:21.540 --> 35:23.590
My wife kicked me out.

35:24.740 --> 35:26.426
I didn't know you were married.

35:27.620 --> 35:30.102
A lot of things you
don't know about me.

35:30.460 --> 35:32.783
I know, Nick. That's the problem.

35:47.060 --> 35:50.942
I'm sorry to have to do this,
but I had no place else to crash.

35:57.780 --> 35:59.591
Who else knows about your wife?

36:01.900 --> 36:03.426
Just...

36:05.620 --> 36:07.659
My friends.

36:07.660 --> 36:09.550
Is that what we are?

36:09.820 --> 36:11.631
That's up to you.

36:12.060 --> 36:13.461
Ahh!

36:15.860 --> 36:17.466
(GROANING)

36:21.340 --> 36:23.344
(COUGHING)

36:29.700 --> 36:33.582
Don't trust anyone.

36:33.740 --> 36:35.949
(DOOR OPENS)

36:36.220 --> 36:37.667
KATE: Captain Rogers?

36:39.340 --> 36:40.619
KATE: Captain,

36:40.620 --> 36:42.899
I'm Agent 13 of S.H.I.E.L.D.
Special Service.

36:42.900 --> 36:44.347
Kate?

36:45.580 --> 36:46.859
I'm assigned to protect you.

36:46.860 --> 36:48.466
ROGERS: On whose order?

36:49.300 --> 36:50.701
(GASPS) His.

36:55.620 --> 36:57.259
Foxtrot is down, he's unresponsive.

36:57.260 --> 36:58.459
I need EMTs.

36:58.460 --> 37:00.385
<i>DISPATCHER:
Do we have a 20 on the shooter?</i>

37:00.660 --> 37:02.391
Tell him I'm in pursuit.

38:02.420 --> 38:03.699
ROMANOFF: Is he gonna make it?

38:03.700 --> 38:05.545
ROGERS: I don't know.

38:06.780 --> 38:08.419
ROMANOFF:
Tell me about the shooter.

38:08.420 --> 38:10.948
He's fast. Strong.

38:13.500 --> 38:15.140
Had a metal arm.

38:20.100 --> 38:21.740
Ballistics?

38:21.980 --> 38:25.619
Three slugs, no rifling.
Completely untraceable.

38:25.620 --> 38:27.306
Soviet-made.

38:27.900 --> 38:29.301
Yeah.

38:29.980 --> 38:31.139
MALE NURSE: He's in V-tach.

38:31.140 --> 38:32.219
FEMALE NURSE: Crash cart coming in.

38:32.220 --> 38:33.259
DOCTOR:
Nurse, help me with the drape.

38:33.260 --> 38:35.340
- MALE NURSE: BP's dropping.
- DOCTOR: Defibrillator!

38:37.220 --> 38:38.859
MALE DOCTOR:
I want you to charge him at 100.

38:38.860 --> 38:40.459
Don't do this to me, Nick.

38:40.460 --> 38:41.939
Stand back.

38:41.940 --> 38:43.419
Three, two,

38:43.420 --> 38:45.390
one. Clear.

38:46.460 --> 38:48.099
- MALE DOCTOR: Pulse?
- MALE NURSE: No pulse.

38:48.100 --> 38:49.379
DOCTOR: Okay, 200, please.

38:49.380 --> 38:50.659
Stand back!

38:50.660 --> 38:53.059
Three, two, one. Clear!

38:53.060 --> 38:54.507
Get me epinephrine!

38:55.380 --> 38:56.419
Pulse?

38:56.420 --> 38:57.821
MALE NURSE: Negative.

39:00.140 --> 39:02.508
Don't do this to me, Nick.
Don't do this to me.

39:22.260 --> 39:23.499
DOCTOR: What's the time?

39:23.500 --> 39:24.981
FEMALE NURSE: 1:03, Doctor.

39:26.780 --> 39:29.865
MALE DOCTOR:
Time of death, 1:03 a.m.

40:06.940 --> 40:08.944
I need to take him.

40:22.500 --> 40:23.981
ROGERS: Natasha.

40:37.420 --> 40:38.867
Natasha!

40:40.140 --> 40:41.780
Why was Fury in your apartment?

40:43.220 --> 40:44.739
(SIGHS) I don't know.

40:44.740 --> 40:46.585
Cap, they want you
back at S.H.I.E.L.D.

40:46.820 --> 40:47.979
Yeah, give me a second.

40:47.980 --> 40:49.381
They want you now.

40:50.340 --> 40:52.071
Okay.

40:54.820 --> 40:57.302
You're a terrible liar.

41:02.980 --> 41:04.899
<i>SITWELL ON EARPIECE: S.T.R.I.K.E.
team, escort Captain Rogers</i>

41:04.900 --> 41:07.379
<i>back to S.H.I.E.L.D.
immediately for questioning.</i>

41:07.380 --> 41:09.270
RUMLOW: I told him.

41:15.980 --> 41:17.745
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

41:19.100 --> 41:20.581
S.T.R.I.K.E., move it out.

41:36.020 --> 41:37.339
Captain Rogers.

41:37.340 --> 41:38.980
Neighbour.

41:40.580 --> 41:42.744
PIERCE: Oh. Captain.

41:42.780 --> 41:44.181
I'm Alexander Pierce.

41:44.420 --> 41:46.059
Sir, it's an honour.

41:46.060 --> 41:47.299
The honour's mine, Captain.

41:47.300 --> 41:50.146
My father served in
the 101st. Come on in.

41:51.060 --> 41:53.779
PIERCE: That photo was taken
five years after Nick and I met,

41:53.780 --> 41:56.339
when I was at State
Department in Bogota.

41:56.340 --> 41:59.019
E.L.N. rebels took the embassy,

41:59.020 --> 42:03.664
and security got me out,
but the rebels took hostages.

42:03.740 --> 42:07.099
Nick was Deputy Chief of the
S.H.I.E.L.D. station there,

42:07.100 --> 42:08.619
and he comes to me with a plan.

42:08.620 --> 42:10.659
He wants to storm the
building through the sewers.

42:10.660 --> 42:13.825
I said, "No, we'll negotiate."

42:14.460 --> 42:18.219
Turned out, the E.L.N. didn't negotiate,
so they put out a kill order.

42:18.220 --> 42:20.539
They stormed the basement,
and what do they find?

42:20.540 --> 42:22.351
They find it empty.

42:23.220 --> 42:25.259
Nick had ignored my direct order,

42:25.260 --> 42:28.982
and carried out an unauthorised
military operation on foreign soil,

42:29.300 --> 42:31.699
and saved the lives of a
dozen political officers,

42:31.700 --> 42:32.979
including my daughter.

42:32.980 --> 42:34.779
So you gave him a promotion.

42:34.780 --> 42:36.705
I've never had any
cause to regret it.

42:38.540 --> 42:41.022
Captain, why was Nick in
your apartment last night?

42:44.700 --> 42:46.181
I don't know.

42:47.020 --> 42:48.751
Did you know it was bugged?

42:49.260 --> 42:51.981
I did, because Nick told me.

42:52.060 --> 42:54.940
Did he tell you he was
the one who bugged it?

43:01.300 --> 43:02.906
I want you to see something.

43:03.460 --> 43:05.019
<i>INTERROGATOR:
Who hired you, Batroc?</i>

43:05.020 --> 43:06.339
Is that live?

43:06.340 --> 43:10.108
Yeah, they picked him up last night
in a not-so-safe house in Algiers.

43:10.820 --> 43:12.379
ROGERS:
Are you saying he's a suspect?

43:12.380 --> 43:14.419
Assassination isn't Batroc's line.

43:14.420 --> 43:17.179
PIERCE: No, no. It's more
complicated than that.

43:17.180 --> 43:19.979
Batroc was hired anonymously
to attack the <i>Lemurian Star</i>.

43:19.980 --> 43:23.862
And he was contacted by email
and paid by wire transfer,

43:24.180 --> 43:28.471
and then the money was run
through 17 fictitious accounts.

43:28.700 --> 43:30.699
The last one going
to a holding company

43:30.700 --> 43:33.099
that was registered
to a Jacob Veech.

43:33.100 --> 43:34.619
Am I supposed to know who that is?

43:34.620 --> 43:37.019
Not likely. Veech
died six years ago.

43:37.020 --> 43:40.151
His last address was
1435 Elmhurst Drive.

43:40.500 --> 43:44.188
When I first met Nick, his
mother lived at 1437.

43:45.460 --> 43:49.148
Are you saying Fury
hired the pirates? Why?

43:49.260 --> 43:51.344
The prevailing theory

43:52.020 --> 43:55.019
was that the hijacking was a
cover for the acquisition

43:55.020 --> 43:57.787
and sale of classified
intelligence.

43:59.220 --> 44:02.430
The sale went sour and
that led to Nick's death.

44:05.180 --> 44:08.345
If you really knew Nick Fury,
you'd know that's not true.

44:09.180 --> 44:11.662
Why do you think we're talking?

44:14.900 --> 44:17.659
See, I took a seat on the Council
not because I wanted to,

44:17.660 --> 44:21.826
but because Nick asked me to,
because we were both realists.

44:22.900 --> 44:27.624
We knew that, despite all the diplomacy
and the handshaking and the rhetoric,

44:28.060 --> 44:30.827
to build a really better world

44:31.140 --> 44:34.703
sometimes means having to
tear the old one down.

44:36.540 --> 44:38.385
And that makes enemies.

44:40.260 --> 44:43.339
Those people that call you
dirty because you got the guts

44:43.340 --> 44:46.505
to stick your hands in the mud and
try to build something better.

44:47.500 --> 44:50.585
And the idea that those
people could be happy today

44:51.660 --> 44:54.506
makes me really, really angry.

44:58.180 --> 45:00.459
Captain, you were the last
one to see Nick alive.

45:00.460 --> 45:02.862
I don't think that's an accident.

45:03.020 --> 45:05.024
And I don't think you do, either.

45:06.860 --> 45:09.059
So, I'm gonna ask again.

45:09.060 --> 45:11.269
Why was he there?

45:13.780 --> 45:16.501
He told me not to trust anyone.

45:18.340 --> 45:20.947
PIERCE:
I wonder if that included him.

45:25.380 --> 45:26.819
I'm sorry.

45:26.820 --> 45:28.506
Those were his last words.

45:29.740 --> 45:31.346
Excuse me.

45:34.380 --> 45:36.019
Captain,

45:36.020 --> 45:39.424
somebody murdered my friend
and I'm gonna find out why.

45:40.060 --> 45:42.906
Anyone gets in my way,
they're gonna regret it.

45:43.860 --> 45:45.671
Anyone.

45:48.180 --> 45:50.025
Understood.

46:07.140 --> 46:08.779
Operations Control.

46:08.780 --> 46:10.545
S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER: Confirmed.

46:11.500 --> 46:13.859
Keep all S.T.R.I.K.E.
personnel on site.

46:13.860 --> 46:15.379
- Understood.
- Yes, sir.

46:15.380 --> 46:16.819
- RUMLOW: Forensics.
<i>- COMPUTER: Confirmed.</i>

46:16.820 --> 46:18.379
RUMLOW: Cap.

46:18.380 --> 46:19.781
Rumlow.

46:28.940 --> 46:31.859
Evidence Response found some fibres
on the roof they want us to see.

46:31.860 --> 46:33.659
You want me to get
the tac team ready?

46:33.660 --> 46:35.379
No, let's wait and see
what it is first.

46:35.380 --> 46:36.861
Right.

46:48.220 --> 46:50.429
What's the status so far?

46:51.220 --> 46:53.270
- MAN: Administrations level.
<i>- COMPUTER: Confirmed.</i>

46:53.420 --> 46:55.265
Excuse me.

46:55.300 --> 46:57.748
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

47:03.100 --> 47:05.579
I'm sorry about what
happened with Fury.

47:05.580 --> 47:07.739
It's messed up, what
happened to him.

47:07.740 --> 47:09.471
Thank you.

47:28.020 --> 47:29.259
MAN: Records.

47:29.260 --> 47:30.786
COMPUTER: Confirmed.

47:46.140 --> 47:48.463
ROGERS: Before we get started,

47:48.780 --> 47:51.182
does anyone want to get out?

47:58.780 --> 48:00.545
(GRUNTING)

48:19.660 --> 48:21.107
(GROANS)

48:22.020 --> 48:23.581
(GRUNTING)

48:24.940 --> 48:27.104
Mobilise S.T.R.I.K.E.
units, 25th floor.

48:41.820 --> 48:43.745
Whoa, big guy.

48:44.460 --> 48:47.545
I just want you to know,
Cap, this isn't personal!

48:55.340 --> 48:56.901
(PANTING)

48:58.900 --> 49:00.426
It kind of feels personal.

49:09.020 --> 49:11.422
Drop the shield and put
your hands in the air!

49:19.140 --> 49:20.871
(GRUNTING)

49:27.740 --> 49:30.620
S.T.R.I.K.E. AGENT: Give it up,
Rogers! Get that door open!

49:30.621 --> 49:32.465
You have nowhere to go!

49:37.020 --> 49:38.706
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

49:38.740 --> 49:40.346
(GROANING)

49:51.900 --> 49:53.059
Are you kidding me?

49:53.060 --> 49:55.622
He's headed for the garage.
Lock down the bridge.

50:06.700 --> 50:10.183
<i>PILOT: Stand down, Captain
Rogers. Stand down.</i>

50:10.260 --> 50:12.822
<i>Repeat, stand down.</i>

50:48.980 --> 50:50.870
SITWELL: Eyes here.

50:50.900 --> 50:52.979
Whatever your op is, bury it.

50:52.980 --> 50:54.381
This is Level One.

50:54.500 --> 50:56.419
Contact DOT.

50:56.420 --> 50:58.390
All traffic lights in
the district go red.

50:58.460 --> 51:00.979
Shut all runways at BWI,

51:00.980 --> 51:02.859
IAD and Reagan.

51:02.860 --> 51:05.911
All security cameras in the city go
through this monitor right here.

51:06.700 --> 51:08.181
Scan all open sources,

51:08.340 --> 51:10.019
phones, computers,

51:10.020 --> 51:11.706
PDAs. Whatever.

51:12.140 --> 51:13.539
If someone tweets about this guy,

51:13.540 --> 51:14.987
I want to know about it.

51:15.300 --> 51:17.059
With all due respect, if
S.H.I.E.L.D. is conducting

51:17.060 --> 51:20.191
a manhunt for Captain America
we deserve to know why.

51:20.340 --> 51:22.105
PIERCE: Because he lied to us.

51:23.340 --> 51:27.222
Captain Rogers has information
regarding the death of Director Fury.

51:27.380 --> 51:29.384
He refused to share it.

51:30.020 --> 51:32.548
As difficult as this is to accept,

51:33.220 --> 51:36.908
Captain America is a
fugitive from S.H.I.E.L.D.

52:04.100 --> 52:05.299
- Where is it?
- Safe.

52:05.300 --> 52:07.139
- Do better.
- Where did you get it?

52:07.140 --> 52:08.579
Why would I tell you?

52:08.580 --> 52:10.819
Fury gave it to you. Why?

52:10.820 --> 52:12.419
- What's on it?
- I don't know.

52:12.420 --> 52:13.619
Stop lying.

52:13.620 --> 52:15.465
I only act like I know
everything, Rogers.

52:16.540 --> 52:18.500
I bet you knew Fury hired
the pirates, didn't you?

52:19.540 --> 52:22.699
Well, it makes sense. The ship was
dirty, Fury needed a way in, so do you.

52:22.700 --> 52:24.306
I'm not gonna ask you again.

52:25.780 --> 52:27.386
I know who killed Fury.

52:30.940 --> 52:33.619
Most of the intelligence community
doesn't believe he exists.

52:33.620 --> 52:36.659
The ones that do call
him the Winter Soldier.

52:36.660 --> 52:38.859
He's credited with over
two dozen assassinations

52:38.860 --> 52:41.149
in the last 50 years.

52:41.220 --> 52:43.099
So he's a ghost story.

52:43.100 --> 52:46.379
Five years ago, I was escorting
a nuclear engineer out of Iran.

52:46.380 --> 52:48.859
Somebody shot out my
tyres near Odessa.

52:48.860 --> 52:51.339
We lost control, went
straight over a cliff.

52:51.340 --> 52:52.819
I pulled us out.

52:52.820 --> 52:55.109
But the Winter Soldier was there.

52:55.460 --> 52:58.099
I was covering my
engineer so he shot him

52:58.100 --> 52:59.501
straight through me.

52:59.940 --> 53:01.421
Soviet slug.

53:01.620 --> 53:04.626
No rifling. Bye-bye, bikinis.

53:05.740 --> 53:08.029
Yeah, I bet you look
terrible in them now.

53:10.340 --> 53:13.266
Going after him is a dead end.
I know, I've tried.

53:14.220 --> 53:16.668
Like you said, he's a ghost story.

53:21.140 --> 53:23.259
Well, let's find out
what the ghost wants.

53:23.260 --> 53:25.788
<i>PIERCE: Nick Fury was
murdered in cold blood.</i>

53:25.860 --> 53:27.379
To any reasonable person,

53:27.380 --> 53:30.099
that would make him a
martyr, not a traitor.

53:30.100 --> 53:31.619
ROCKWELL:
You know what makes him a traitor?

53:31.620 --> 53:34.139
Hiring a mercenary to
hijack his own ship.

53:34.140 --> 53:36.619
SINGH:
Nick Fury used your friendship

53:36.620 --> 53:39.899
to coerce this Council into
delaying Project Insight.

53:39.900 --> 53:42.499
A project he knew would expose
his own illegal operations.

53:42.500 --> 53:45.579
At best, he lied
to you. At worst...

53:45.580 --> 53:48.099
Are you calling for my resignation?

53:48.100 --> 53:49.699
I've got a pen and
paper right here.

53:49.700 --> 53:52.626
That discussion can be
tabled for a later time.

53:53.420 --> 53:55.139
But you do want to
have a discussion?

53:55.140 --> 53:57.463
We've already had it, Mr Secretary.

53:58.140 --> 54:02.943
This Council moves to immediately
reactivate Project Insight.

54:03.820 --> 54:07.588
If you want to say something
snappy, now would be a good time.

54:13.300 --> 54:16.988
First rule of going on the
run is don't run, walk.

54:17.340 --> 54:20.061
If I run in these shoes,
they're gonna fall off.

54:22.700 --> 54:25.339
The drive has a Level Six homing
program, so as soon as we boot up

54:25.340 --> 54:27.299
S.H.I.E.L.D. will know
exactly where we are.

54:27.300 --> 54:28.747
How much time will we have?

54:28.820 --> 54:31.427
About nine minutes from

54:32.660 --> 54:34.107
now.

54:39.020 --> 54:40.859
ROMANOFF:
Fury was right about that ship.

54:40.860 --> 54:43.139
Somebody's trying
to hide something.

54:43.140 --> 54:45.339
This drive is protected
by some sort of Al.

54:45.340 --> 54:47.899
It keeps rewriting itself
to counter my commands.

54:47.900 --> 54:49.950
Can you override it?

54:50.300 --> 54:52.668
The person who developed this
is slightly smarter than me.

54:52.900 --> 54:54.461
Slightly.

55:04.900 --> 55:06.506
I'm gonna try running a tracer.

55:07.220 --> 55:09.019
This is a program that
S.H.I.E.L.D. developed

55:09.020 --> 55:10.539
to track hostile malware,

55:10.540 --> 55:13.579
so if we can't read the file,

55:13.580 --> 55:15.550
maybe we can find out
where it came from.

55:15.740 --> 55:17.141
Can I help you guys with anything?

55:17.540 --> 55:21.299
Oh, no. My fiancé was just helping
me with some honeymoon destinations.

55:21.300 --> 55:23.459
Right. We're getting married.

55:23.460 --> 55:25.701
Congratulations. Where are you
guys thinking about going?

55:27.260 --> 55:29.150
- New Jersey.
- Oh.

55:33.700 --> 55:35.750
I have the exact same glasses.

55:36.260 --> 55:38.179
Wow, you two are practically twins.

55:38.180 --> 55:39.991
Yeah, I wish.

55:40.100 --> 55:41.501
Specimen.

55:41.780 --> 55:43.939
If you guys need anything,
I've been Aaron.

55:43.940 --> 55:45.341
Thank you.

55:47.420 --> 55:50.187
- You said nine minutes. Come on.
- Relax.

55:51.020 --> 55:52.501
Got it.

55:56.260 --> 55:57.419
You know it?

55:57.420 --> 55:59.390
I used to. Let's go.

56:01.140 --> 56:02.579
Standard tac team.

56:02.580 --> 56:04.099
Two behind, two across,

56:04.100 --> 56:05.899
and two coming straight at us.

56:05.900 --> 56:08.779
If they make us, I'll engage, you hit
the south escalator to the metro.

56:08.780 --> 56:10.939
Shut up and put your arm around me.
Laugh at something I said.

56:10.940 --> 56:12.580
- What?
- Do it.

56:12.820 --> 56:14.745
(ROGERS LAUGHING)

56:20.460 --> 56:21.619
Negative at the source.

56:21.620 --> 56:23.021
Give me a floor rundown.

56:23.140 --> 56:24.699
<i>(OVER RADIO) Negative on three.</i>

56:24.700 --> 56:26.059
<i>(OVER RADIO) Negative on two.</i>

56:26.060 --> 56:28.701
Snake the upper levels.
Work down to me.

56:36.340 --> 56:37.539
- Kiss me.
- What?

56:37.540 --> 56:39.739
Public displays of affection
make people very uncomfortable.

56:39.740 --> 56:41.266
Yes, they do.

56:50.340 --> 56:52.310
You still uncomfortable?

56:52.820 --> 56:54.745
It's not exactly the
word I would use.

57:03.460 --> 57:05.988
Where did Captain America
learn how to steal a car?

57:06.540 --> 57:08.499
- Nazi Germany.
- Mmm.

57:08.500 --> 57:10.948
And we're borrowing.
Take your feet off the dash.

57:14.820 --> 57:18.579
All right, I have a question for you,
which you do not have to answer.

57:18.580 --> 57:20.019
I feel like, if you
don't answer it though,

57:20.020 --> 57:21.579
- you're kind of answering it, you know.
- What?

57:21.580 --> 57:24.460
Was that your first
kiss since 1945?

57:24.580 --> 57:26.179
- That bad, huh?
- I didn't say that.

57:26.180 --> 57:27.899
Well, it kind of sounds like
that's what you're saying.

57:27.900 --> 57:29.059
No, I didn't.

57:29.060 --> 57:31.179
I just wondered how much
practice you've had.

57:31.180 --> 57:33.019
- You don't need practice.
- Everybody needs practice.

57:33.020 --> 57:35.659
It was not my first
kiss since 1945.

57:35.660 --> 57:37.789
I'm 95, I'm not dead.

57:37.940 --> 57:39.539
Nobody special, though?

57:39.540 --> 57:41.271
(CHUCKLES)

57:41.700 --> 57:42.859
Believe it or not,
it's kind of hard

57:42.860 --> 57:45.259
to find someone with
shared life experience.

57:45.260 --> 57:47.260
Well, that's all right.
You just make something up.

57:47.300 --> 57:49.419
- What, like you?
- I don't know.

57:49.420 --> 57:50.699
The truth is a matter
of circumstance.

57:50.700 --> 57:53.467
It's not all things to all
people, all the time.

57:54.380 --> 57:55.781
Neither am I.

57:56.140 --> 57:57.780
That's a tough way to live.

57:58.620 --> 58:01.102
It's a good way not to die, though.

58:01.580 --> 58:03.219
You know, it's kind of
hard to trust someone,

58:03.220 --> 58:05.110
when you don't know who
that someone really is.

58:05.780 --> 58:07.261
Yeah.

58:10.060 --> 58:11.541
Who do you want me to be?

58:12.100 --> 58:13.501
How about a friend?

58:16.580 --> 58:21.065
Well, there's a chance you might
be in the wrong business, Rogers.

58:36.420 --> 58:38.231
ROGERS: This is it.

58:39.060 --> 58:41.383
The file came from
these coordinates.

58:42.260 --> 58:43.866
So did I.

58:51.660 --> 58:53.505
This camp is where I was trained.

58:56.140 --> 58:57.701
Change much?

58:59.940 --> 59:01.379
A little.

59:01.380 --> 59:03.699
DRILL SERGEANT:
Pick up the pace, ladies!

59:03.700 --> 59:05.704
Let's go! Let's go!

59:06.140 --> 59:07.780
Double time!

59:08.660 --> 59:11.062
Come on, Rogers, move it!

59:14.700 --> 59:16.431
Come on, fall in!

59:17.060 --> 59:18.541
Rogers!

59:18.580 --> 59:20.220
I said fall in!

59:22.140 --> 59:23.459
ROMANOFF: This is a dead end.

59:23.460 --> 59:26.670
Zero heat signatures, zero
waves, not even radio.

59:27.700 --> 59:30.944
Whoever wrote the file must have
used a router to throw people off.

59:32.500 --> 59:33.699
What is it?

59:33.700 --> 59:35.699
ROGERS: Army regulations
forbid storing munitions

59:35.700 --> 59:38.023
within 500 yards of the barracks.

59:38.420 --> 59:40.868
This building is in
the wrong place.

59:55.860 --> 59:58.069
ROMANOFF: This is S.H.I.E.L.D.

59:58.540 --> 01:00:00.863
Maybe where it started.

01:00:18.540 --> 01:00:20.669
And there's Stark's father.

01:00:20.860 --> 01:00:22.625
ROGERS: Howard.

01:00:23.540 --> 01:00:25.180
Who's the girl?

01:00:44.180 --> 01:00:46.901
If you're already working
in a secret office,

01:00:57.060 --> 01:00:58.739
why do you need to
hide the elevator?

01:00:58.740 --> 01:01:00.141
(MACHINE BLEEPING)

01:01:07.100 --> 01:01:08.786
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:01:50.380 --> 01:01:54.546
This can't be the data point.
This technology is ancient.

01:02:18.660 --> 01:02:21.461
(ELECTRONIC VOICE SPEAKING)

01:02:24.100 --> 01:02:26.502
Y-E-S spells yes.

01:02:27.060 --> 01:02:29.064
(POWERING UP)

01:02:30.180 --> 01:02:32.503
Shall we play a game?

01:02:32.700 --> 01:02:35.501
- It's from a movie that was really...
- I know, I saw it.

01:02:35.660 --> 01:02:37.061
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

01:02:41.340 --> 01:02:43.708
<i>Rogers, Steven,</i>

01:02:44.340 --> 01:02:46.424
<i>born 1918.</i>

01:02:49.180 --> 01:02:52.099
<i>Romanoff, Natalia Alianovna,</i>

01:02:52.100 --> 01:02:54.139
<i>born 1984.</i>

01:02:54.140 --> 01:02:55.699
It's some kind of recording.

01:02:55.700 --> 01:02:58.421
<i>I am not a recording, Fräulein.</i>

01:02:58.700 --> 01:03:00.699
<i>I may not be the man I was</i>

01:03:00.700 --> 01:03:04.263
<i>when the Captain took
me prisoner in 1945.</i>

01:03:04.380 --> 01:03:06.384
<i>But I am.</i>

01:03:07.820 --> 01:03:09.665
You know this thing?

01:03:12.660 --> 01:03:16.059
ROGERS: Arnim Zola was a German
scientist who worked for the Red Skull.

01:03:16.060 --> 01:03:17.299
He's been dead for years.

01:03:17.300 --> 01:03:19.987
<i>ZOLA: First correction, I am Swiss.</i>

01:03:20.020 --> 01:03:22.539
<i>Second, look around you.</i>

01:03:22.540 --> 01:03:25.591
<i>I have never been more alive.</i>

01:03:25.700 --> 01:03:30.219
<i>In 1972, I received a
terminal diagnosis.</i>

01:03:30.220 --> 01:03:33.259
<i>Science could not save my body.</i>

01:03:33.260 --> 01:03:37.619
<i>My mind, however,
that was worth saving,</i>

01:03:37.620 --> 01:03:41.579
<i>on 200,000 feet of databanks.</i>

01:03:41.580 --> 01:03:45.379
<i>You are standing in my brain.</i>

01:03:45.380 --> 01:03:47.987
- ROGERS: How did you get here?
<i>- Invited.</i>

01:03:48.220 --> 01:03:50.619
It was Operation Paperclip
after World War II.

01:03:50.620 --> 01:03:54.419
S.H.I.E.L.D. recruited German
scientists with strategic value.

01:03:54.420 --> 01:03:56.739
<i>ZOLA: They thought I
could help their cause.</i>

01:03:56.740 --> 01:03:58.819
<i>I also helped my own.</i>

01:03:58.820 --> 01:04:00.539
ROGERS:
HYDRA died with the Red Skull.

01:04:00.540 --> 01:04:04.831
<i>Cut off one head, two more
shall take its place.</i>

01:04:04.860 --> 01:04:06.671
Prove it.

01:04:07.620 --> 01:04:09.943
<i>Accessing archive.</i>

01:04:10.100 --> 01:04:13.619
<i>HYDRA was founded on the
belief that humanity</i>

01:04:13.620 --> 01:04:16.979
<i>could not be trusted
with its own freedom.</i>

01:04:16.980 --> 01:04:19.859
<i>What we did not realise
was that if you try</i>

01:04:19.860 --> 01:04:23.070
<i>to take that freedom, they resist.</i>

01:04:23.540 --> 01:04:25.465
<i>The war taught us much.</i>

01:04:25.660 --> 01:04:29.348
<i>Humanity needed to surrender
its freedom willingly.</i>

01:04:30.100 --> 01:04:33.019
<i>After the war,
S.H.I.E.L.D. was founded,</i>

01:04:33.020 --> 01:04:35.548
<i>and I was recruited.</i>

01:04:35.580 --> 01:04:37.779
<i>The new HYDRA grew.</i>

01:04:37.780 --> 01:04:42.459
<i>A beautiful parasite
inside S.H.I.E.L.D.</i>

01:04:42.460 --> 01:04:44.299
<i>For 70 years,</i>

01:04:44.300 --> 01:04:50.139
<i>HYDRA has been secretly
feeding crisis, reaping war,</i>

01:04:50.140 --> 01:04:53.225
<i>and when history did not cooperate,</i>

01:04:53.660 --> 01:04:55.659
<i>history was changed.</i>

01:04:55.660 --> 01:04:57.939
That's impossible. S.H.I.E.L.D.
would have stopped you.

01:04:57.940 --> 01:05:00.741
<i>Accidents will happen.</i>

01:05:02.340 --> 01:05:05.379
<i>HYDRA created a world so chaotic</i>

01:05:05.380 --> 01:05:09.539
<i>that humanity is finally ready
to sacrifice its freedom</i>

01:05:09.540 --> 01:05:11.942
<i>to gain its security.</i>

01:05:12.340 --> 01:05:15.983
<i>Once a purification
process is complete,</i>

01:05:16.140 --> 01:05:19.908
<i>HYDRA's new world order will arise.</i>

01:05:20.420 --> 01:05:22.499
<i>We won, Captain.</i>

01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:26.427
<i>Your death amounts to
the same as your life.</i>

01:05:26.500 --> 01:05:27.947
<i>A zero sum.</i>

01:05:28.180 --> 01:05:29.459
(GRUNTS)

01:05:29.460 --> 01:05:31.066
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

01:05:31.180 --> 01:05:33.469
<i>As I was saying...</i>

01:05:33.900 --> 01:05:35.179
What's on this drive?

01:05:35.180 --> 01:05:38.823
<i>Project Insight requires insight.</i>

01:05:38.900 --> 01:05:41.819
<i>So, I wrote an algorithm.</i>

01:05:41.820 --> 01:05:43.179
What kind of algorithm?
What does it do?

01:05:43.180 --> 01:05:46.106
<i>The answer to your
question is fascinating.</i>

01:05:46.140 --> 01:05:50.379
<i>Unfortunately, you shall
be too dead to hear it.</i>

01:05:50.380 --> 01:05:52.066
(DOOR CLOSING)

01:05:53.420 --> 01:05:55.265
(CELL PHONE BEEPING)

01:05:56.020 --> 01:05:57.865
Steve, we got a bogey.

01:05:57.900 --> 01:05:59.779
Short range ballistic.

01:05:59.780 --> 01:06:01.539
- 30 seconds tops.
- Who fired it?

01:06:01.540 --> 01:06:02.699
S.H.I.E.L.D.

01:06:02.700 --> 01:06:06.866
<i>I am afraid I have been
stalling, Captain.</i>

01:06:06.980 --> 01:06:08.219
<i>Admit it.</i>

01:06:08.220 --> 01:06:10.659
<i>It's better this way.</i>

01:06:10.660 --> 01:06:12.471
<i>We are, both of us,</i>

01:06:13.380 --> 01:06:15.020
<i>out of time.</i>

01:06:30.580 --> 01:06:33.062
(DEBRIS SETTLING)

01:06:41.100 --> 01:06:43.379
(ROGERS GROANING)

01:06:43.380 --> 01:06:45.748
(GRUNTING)

01:06:50.020 --> 01:06:51.859
(PANTING)

01:06:51.860 --> 01:06:54.228
(COUGHING)

01:07:38.060 --> 01:07:39.985
Call in the asset.

01:07:55.820 --> 01:07:57.585
RENATA: I'm going to go, Mr Pierce.

01:07:57.740 --> 01:07:59.949
You need anything before I leave?

01:08:00.340 --> 01:08:04.028
No... Uh, it's fine,
Renata, you can go home.

01:08:04.260 --> 01:08:06.179
Okay. Night-night.

01:08:06.180 --> 01:08:08.230
Good night.

01:08:10.460 --> 01:08:12.350
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:08:12.980 --> 01:08:14.745
Want some milk?

01:08:23.980 --> 01:08:26.223
The timetable has moved.

01:08:27.980 --> 01:08:30.109
Our window is limited.

01:08:33.740 --> 01:08:36.268
Two targets, Level Six.

01:08:37.340 --> 01:08:39.739
They already cost me Zola.

01:08:39.740 --> 01:08:42.347
I want confirmed death in 10 hours.

01:08:43.900 --> 01:08:46.428
Sorry, Mr Pierce, I...

01:08:46.540 --> 01:08:48.059
I forgot my

01:08:48.060 --> 01:08:49.586
phone.

01:08:54.220 --> 01:08:57.749
Oh, Renata, I wish you
would have knocked.

01:08:58.540 --> 01:09:00.465
- (GUN FIRING)
- (RENATA SHRIEKS)

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:12.859
(PANTING)

01:09:12.860 --> 01:09:15.262
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

01:09:21.900 --> 01:09:23.059
Hey, man.

01:09:23.060 --> 01:09:26.779
I'm sorry about this. We
need a place to lay low.

01:09:26.780 --> 01:09:28.830
Everyone we know is
trying to kill us.

01:09:31.380 --> 01:09:33.270
Not everyone.

01:09:49.860 --> 01:09:51.944
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:10:00.460 --> 01:10:02.350
What's going on?

01:10:05.220 --> 01:10:09.022
When I first joined S.H.I.E.L.D.
I thought I was going straight.

01:10:12.460 --> 01:10:15.784
But I guess I just traded
in the KGB for HYDRA.

01:10:20.060 --> 01:10:21.259
(SIGHS)

01:10:21.260 --> 01:10:23.742
I thought I knew whose
lies I was telling,

01:10:27.140 --> 01:10:30.305
but I guess I can't tell
the difference any more.

01:10:30.940 --> 01:10:33.263
There's a chance you might
be in the wrong business.

01:10:38.140 --> 01:10:39.621
I owe you.

01:10:40.780 --> 01:10:42.227
It's okay.

01:10:42.380 --> 01:10:44.987
If it was the other way around,

01:10:45.820 --> 01:10:47.499
and it was down to me
to save your life,

01:10:47.500 --> 01:10:49.390
now you be honest with me,

01:10:51.180 --> 01:10:53.469
would you trust me to do it?

01:10:55.220 --> 01:10:56.621
I would now.

01:10:59.260 --> 01:11:01.424
And I'm always honest.

01:11:02.340 --> 01:11:03.659
Well, you seem pretty chipper

01:11:03.660 --> 01:11:05.744
for someone who just found
out they died for nothing.

01:11:06.260 --> 01:11:10.346
Well, guess I just like
to know who I'm fighting.

01:11:10.820 --> 01:11:12.221
WILSON: I made breakfast.

01:11:12.460 --> 01:11:15.784
If you guys eat that sort of thing.

01:11:16.980 --> 01:11:18.539
So, the question is,

01:11:18.540 --> 01:11:20.942
who at S.H.I.E.L.D. could launch
a domestic missile strike?

01:11:22.620 --> 01:11:23.899
Pierce.

01:11:23.900 --> 01:11:26.699
Who happens to be sitting on top of the
most secure building in the world.

01:11:26.700 --> 01:11:28.059
But he's not working alone.

01:11:28.060 --> 01:11:30.781
Zola's algorithm was
on the <i>Lemurian Star</i>.

01:11:31.540 --> 01:11:33.430
So was Jasper Sitwell.

01:11:36.700 --> 01:11:39.219
So, the real question is, how
do the two most wanted people

01:11:39.220 --> 01:11:42.544
in Washington kidnap a S.H.I.E.L.D.
officer in broad daylight?

01:11:42.980 --> 01:11:45.269
The answer is, you don't.

01:11:45.820 --> 01:11:47.949
- What's this?
- Call it a résumé.

01:11:51.220 --> 01:11:52.979
Is this Bakhmala?

01:11:52.980 --> 01:11:54.791
The Khalid Khandil
mission, that was you?

01:11:56.140 --> 01:11:57.951
You didn't say he was a Pararescue.

01:11:59.300 --> 01:12:01.619
- Is this Riley?
- Yeah.

01:12:01.620 --> 01:12:04.261
ROMANOFF: I heard they couldn't bring
in the choppers because of the RPGs.

01:12:04.340 --> 01:12:05.379
What did you use? A stealth chute?

01:12:05.380 --> 01:12:06.827
No.

01:12:07.140 --> 01:12:08.985
These.

01:12:13.500 --> 01:12:15.099
I thought you said
you were a pilot.

01:12:15.100 --> 01:12:16.831
I never said pilot.

01:12:20.420 --> 01:12:22.584
I can't ask you to do this, Sam.

01:12:22.780 --> 01:12:24.419
You got out for a good reason.

01:12:24.420 --> 01:12:26.139
Dude, Captain America
needs my help.

01:12:26.140 --> 01:12:28.065
There's no better
reason to get back in.

01:12:31.420 --> 01:12:33.299
Where can we get our hands
on one of these things?

01:12:33.300 --> 01:12:34.826
The last one is at Fort Meade.

01:12:35.460 --> 01:12:38.386
Behind three guarded gates
and a 12-inch steel wall.

01:12:41.020 --> 01:12:42.546
Shouldn't be a problem.

01:12:43.860 --> 01:12:45.659
Listen, I got to fly home tonight

01:12:45.660 --> 01:12:48.619
because I got some
constituency problem

01:12:48.620 --> 01:12:50.739
and I got to press the flesh.

01:12:50.740 --> 01:12:53.427
Any constituent in
particular, Mr Senator?

01:12:53.580 --> 01:12:55.391
Oh, no, not really.

01:12:55.940 --> 01:12:58.229
Twenty-three, kind of hot.

01:12:58.500 --> 01:12:59.819
Real hot, you know?

01:12:59.820 --> 01:13:02.179
Wants to be a reporter,
I think. I don't know.

01:13:02.180 --> 01:13:03.379
Who listens at that point?

01:13:03.380 --> 01:13:05.219
Doesn't sound like much
of a problem to me.

01:13:05.220 --> 01:13:07.702
Really? Because she's
killing my back.

01:13:08.260 --> 01:13:10.219
But this isn't the place
to talk about it.

01:13:10.220 --> 01:13:11.667
This is a nice pin.

01:13:12.540 --> 01:13:15.068
- Thank you.
- Come here.

01:13:15.460 --> 01:13:17.225
(WHISPERS) Hail HYDRA.

01:13:19.980 --> 01:13:22.223
- See, it's right there...
- Yeah, I just saw that.

01:13:22.740 --> 01:13:24.665
- Should I get it checked?
- I think you should.

01:13:26.900 --> 01:13:28.825
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

01:13:33.020 --> 01:13:34.379
I need a minute.

01:13:34.380 --> 01:13:36.430
Bring the car around.

01:13:39.660 --> 01:13:40.899
Yes, sir?

01:13:40.900 --> 01:13:42.779
<i>WILSON:
Agent Sitwell, how was lunch?</i>

01:13:42.780 --> 01:13:45.499
<i>I hear the crab cakes
here are delicious.</i>

01:13:45.500 --> 01:13:46.699
Who is this?

01:13:46.700 --> 01:13:49.785
<i>The good-looking guy in the
sunglasses, your 10 o'clock.</i>

01:13:51.500 --> 01:13:53.026
<i>Your other 10 o'clock.</i>

01:13:54.500 --> 01:13:55.901
<i>There you go.</i>

01:13:58.340 --> 01:14:00.059
What do you want?

01:14:00.060 --> 01:14:02.059
<i>You're gonna go around the
corner to your right.</i>

01:14:02.060 --> 01:14:04.779
There's a grey car two spaces down.

01:14:04.780 --> 01:14:06.819
You and I are gonna take a ride.

01:14:06.820 --> 01:14:08.699
And Why would I do that?

01:14:08.700 --> 01:14:11.706
Because that tie looks
really expensive,

01:14:11.740 --> 01:14:14.108
<i>and I'd hate to mess it up.</i>

01:14:20.380 --> 01:14:22.623
(GRUNTING)

01:14:23.300 --> 01:14:24.940
Tell me about Zola's algorithm.

01:14:25.620 --> 01:14:26.699
Never heard of it.

01:14:26.700 --> 01:14:27.819
What were you doing
on the <i>Lemurian Star</i>?

01:14:27.820 --> 01:14:29.949
I was throwing up. I get seasick.

01:14:30.340 --> 01:14:31.946
(GASPS)

01:14:34.740 --> 01:14:38.349
Is this little display meant to insinuate
that you're gonna throw me off the roof?

01:14:39.060 --> 01:14:40.871
Because it's really not
your style, Rogers.

01:14:41.740 --> 01:14:43.141
You're right.

01:14:43.620 --> 01:14:45.067
It's not.

01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:46.581
It's hers.

01:14:47.740 --> 01:14:49.380
(SCREAMING)

01:14:50.100 --> 01:14:53.106
Oh, wait. What about that girl
from Accounting, Laura...

01:14:53.220 --> 01:14:55.139
Lillian. Lip piercing, right?

01:14:55.140 --> 01:14:56.419
Yeah, she's cute.

01:14:56.420 --> 01:14:58.059
Yeah. I'm not ready for that.

01:14:58.060 --> 01:15:00.579
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

01:15:00.580 --> 01:15:02.220
(GROANS)

01:15:09.780 --> 01:15:12.262
Zola's algorithm is a program

01:15:13.540 --> 01:15:14.859
for choosing

01:15:14.860 --> 01:15:16.779
- Insight's targets.
- What targets?

01:15:16.780 --> 01:15:18.261
You!

01:15:18.860 --> 01:15:21.419
A TV anchor in Cairo, the
Under Secretary of Defence,

01:15:21.420 --> 01:15:24.099
a high school Valedictorian
in Iowa City,

01:15:24.100 --> 01:15:26.419
Bruce Banner, Stephen Strange,
anyone who's a threat

01:15:26.420 --> 01:15:28.219
to HYDRA.

01:15:28.220 --> 01:15:30.259
Now, or in the future.

01:15:30.260 --> 01:15:32.424
In the future? How could it know?

01:15:34.020 --> 01:15:35.619
(LAUGHING)

01:15:35.620 --> 01:15:37.067
How could it not?

01:15:38.780 --> 01:15:42.548
The 21st century is a digital book.

01:15:43.460 --> 01:15:45.703
Zola taught HYDRA how to read it.

01:15:48.220 --> 01:15:49.746
Your bank records,

01:15:49.780 --> 01:15:51.379
medical histories, voting patterns,

01:15:51.380 --> 01:15:54.226
emails, phone calls,
your damn SAT scores!

01:15:55.340 --> 01:15:59.108
Zola's algorithm
evaluates people's past

01:15:59.580 --> 01:16:01.139
to predict their future.

01:16:01.140 --> 01:16:02.587
And what then?

01:16:05.620 --> 01:16:07.499
Oh, my God. Pierce
is gonna kill me.

01:16:07.500 --> 01:16:09.425
What then?

01:16:11.620 --> 01:16:15.103
Then the Insight helicarriers
scratch people off the list.

01:16:16.940 --> 01:16:19.183
A few million at a time.

01:16:26.420 --> 01:16:27.659
SITWELL: HYDRA doesn't like leaks.

01:16:27.660 --> 01:16:29.539
Then why don't you try
sticking a cork in it?

01:16:29.540 --> 01:16:31.019
Insight's launching in 16 hours.

01:16:31.020 --> 01:16:32.259
We're cutting it a
little bit close here.

01:16:32.260 --> 01:16:34.339
I know. We'll use him
to bypass the DNA scans

01:16:34.340 --> 01:16:35.979
and access the
helicarriers directly.

01:16:35.980 --> 01:16:37.427
What? Are you crazy?

01:16:37.900 --> 01:16:40.029
- That is a terrible, terrible idea.
- (THUD)

01:16:41.020 --> 01:16:42.660
(SCREAMING)

01:16:48.860 --> 01:16:50.625
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

01:17:15.540 --> 01:17:17.942
(BRAKES SQUEALING)

01:17:23.300 --> 01:17:24.906
(SCREAMING) Shit!

01:17:35.900 --> 01:17:37.379
ROGERS: Hang on!

01:17:37.380 --> 01:17:38.827
(GRUNTS)

01:17:50.540 --> 01:17:51.941
(BRAKES SCREECH)

01:18:02.260 --> 01:18:03.619
(HORN BLARES)

01:18:03.620 --> 01:18:05.260
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:18:45.500 --> 01:18:46.981
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:19:16.020 --> 01:19:17.659
(WINTER SOLDIER SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

01:19:17.660 --> 01:19:21.030
I have her. Find him.

01:20:00.620 --> 01:20:02.101
(GRUNTS)

01:20:02.700 --> 01:20:04.340
(SCREAMS)

01:20:25.900 --> 01:20:27.299
Go! I got this!

01:20:27.300 --> 01:20:28.747
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:20:44.940 --> 01:20:46.785
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:20:54.780 --> 01:20:56.181
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

01:21:06.940 --> 01:21:08.779
<i>ROMANOFF: Taking fire above
and below expressway.</i>

01:21:08.780 --> 01:21:11.660
<i>Civilians threatened. Repeat,
civilians threatened.</i>

01:21:15.420 --> 01:21:18.299
<i>I make an LZ, 2300 block
of Virginia Avenue.</i>

01:21:18.300 --> 01:21:19.781
<i>Rendezvous, two minutes.</i>

01:21:44.820 --> 01:21:46.221
Get out of the way!

01:21:46.380 --> 01:21:48.384
Stay out of the way!

01:21:49.460 --> 01:21:51.305
- (GUNSHOT)
- Ahh!

01:23:35.060 --> 01:23:36.507
Bucky?

01:23:36.660 --> 01:23:38.505
Who the hell is Bucky?

01:23:51.060 --> 01:23:53.064
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:24:06.780 --> 01:24:08.459
Drop the shield, Cap!
Get on your knees!

01:24:08.460 --> 01:24:10.139
- Get on your knees!
- (ALL SHOUTING)

01:24:10.140 --> 01:24:12.779
Get down, get down!
Get on your knees!

01:24:12.780 --> 01:24:14.341
Down!

01:24:14.460 --> 01:24:15.861
Don't move.

01:24:22.460 --> 01:24:23.939
Put the gun down.

01:24:23.940 --> 01:24:26.263
Not here. Not here!

01:24:41.380 --> 01:24:42.827
ROGERS: It was him.

01:24:45.660 --> 01:24:49.587
He looked right at me like
he didn't even know me.

01:24:49.700 --> 01:24:52.619
How is that even possible?
It was, like, 70 years ago.

01:24:52.620 --> 01:24:54.019
Zola.

01:24:54.020 --> 01:24:55.859
Bucky's whole unit
was captured in '43.

01:24:55.860 --> 01:24:57.899
Zola experimented on him.

01:24:57.900 --> 01:25:00.587
Whatever he did helped
Bucky survive the fall.

01:25:01.900 --> 01:25:03.259
They must have found him and...

01:25:03.260 --> 01:25:05.583
None of that's your fault, Steve.

01:25:08.820 --> 01:25:10.949
Even when I had
nothing, I had Bucky.

01:25:13.860 --> 01:25:15.779
We need to get a doctor here.

01:25:15.780 --> 01:25:16.979
If we don't put
pressure on that wound,

01:25:16.980 --> 01:25:18.711
she's gonna bleed out
here in the truck.

01:25:21.860 --> 01:25:23.625
(GROANING)

01:25:25.860 --> 01:25:29.423
Ah. That thing was
squeezing my brain.

01:25:32.100 --> 01:25:33.581
Who is this guy?

01:25:43.980 --> 01:25:46.348
Three holes. Start digging.

01:26:13.100 --> 01:26:15.219
HILL:
GSW. She's lost at least a pint.

01:26:15.220 --> 01:26:16.579
WILSON: Maybe two.

01:26:16.580 --> 01:26:18.982
- Let me take her.
- She'll want to see him first.

01:26:28.500 --> 01:26:31.141
About damn time.

01:26:32.700 --> 01:26:34.704
Lacerated spinal column,

01:26:34.940 --> 01:26:36.339
cracked sternum,

01:26:36.340 --> 01:26:38.099
shattered collarbone,

01:26:38.100 --> 01:26:39.939
perforated liver,

01:26:39.940 --> 01:26:41.939
and one hell of a headache.

01:26:41.940 --> 01:26:43.499
Don't forget your collapsed lung.

01:26:43.500 --> 01:26:44.979
Let's not forget that.

01:26:44.980 --> 01:26:46.979
Otherwise, I'm good.

01:26:46.980 --> 01:26:49.339
They cut you open.
Your heart stopped.

01:26:49.340 --> 01:26:51.579
Tetrodotoxin B.

01:26:51.580 --> 01:26:53.739
Slows the pulse to
one beat a minute.

01:26:53.740 --> 01:26:55.739
Banner developed it for stress.

01:26:55.740 --> 01:26:58.539
Didn't work so great for him,
but we found a use for it.

01:26:58.540 --> 01:27:00.619
Why all the secrecy?
Why not just tell us?

01:27:00.620 --> 01:27:03.307
Any attempt on the Director's
life had to look successful.

01:27:03.380 --> 01:27:05.939
Can't kill you if
you're already dead.

01:27:05.940 --> 01:27:07.421
Besides,

01:27:08.300 --> 01:27:10.225
I wasn't sure who to trust.

01:27:25.340 --> 01:27:27.071
Sergeant Barnes.

01:27:28.820 --> 01:27:29.939
Bucky, no!

01:27:29.940 --> 01:27:31.671
(BUCKY SCREAMING)

01:27:33.540 --> 01:27:37.023
<i>ZOLA:
The procedure has already started.</i>

01:27:40.500 --> 01:27:44.579
<i>You are to be the
new fist of HYDRA.</i>

01:27:44.580 --> 01:27:45.981
<i>Put him on ice.</i>

01:27:56.980 --> 01:27:58.381
Sir.

01:27:58.700 --> 01:28:00.590
(STAMMERS) He's unstable.

01:28:00.700 --> 01:28:02.511
Erratic.

01:28:15.380 --> 01:28:16.861
Mission report.

01:28:19.980 --> 01:28:21.711
Mission report now.

01:28:34.100 --> 01:28:35.911
The man on the bridge.

01:28:37.060 --> 01:28:38.659
(INAUDIBLE)

01:28:38.660 --> 01:28:40.300
Who was he?

01:28:41.300 --> 01:28:43.987
You met him earlier this
week on another assignment.

01:28:46.660 --> 01:28:48.391
I knew him.

01:28:56.580 --> 01:28:59.665
Your work has been
a gift to mankind.

01:29:01.540 --> 01:29:03.351
You shaped the century.

01:29:03.620 --> 01:29:06.500
And I need you to do
it one more time.

01:29:07.380 --> 01:29:11.259
Society's at a tipping point
between order and chaos.

01:29:11.260 --> 01:29:14.345
And tomorrow morning,
we're gonna give it a push.

01:29:15.060 --> 01:29:18.669
But, if you don't do your
part, I can't do mine.

01:29:19.940 --> 01:29:23.184
And HYDRA can't give the world
the freedom it deserves.

01:29:25.820 --> 01:29:27.824
But I knew him.

01:29:27.940 --> 01:29:29.501
(SIGHS)

01:29:33.940 --> 01:29:35.659
PIERCE: Prep him.

01:29:35.660 --> 01:29:38.459
He's been out of cryo
freeze too long.

01:29:38.460 --> 01:29:40.862
Then wipe him and start over.

01:30:08.660 --> 01:30:10.949
(SCREAMING)

01:30:22.180 --> 01:30:26.141
This man declined the
Nobel Peace Prize.

01:30:26.500 --> 01:30:30.143
He said peace wasn't
an achievement,

01:30:30.220 --> 01:30:32.702
it was a responsibility.

01:30:33.300 --> 01:30:36.943
See, it's stuff like this
that gives me trust issues.

01:30:37.300 --> 01:30:38.940
We have to stop the launch.

01:30:39.500 --> 01:30:42.665
I don't think the Council's
accepting my calls any more.

01:30:44.780 --> 01:30:46.219
What's that?

01:30:46.220 --> 01:30:48.979
Once the helicarriers
reach 3,000 feet,

01:30:48.980 --> 01:30:52.748
they'll triangulate with Insight
satellites, becoming fully weaponised.

01:30:53.020 --> 01:30:54.899
FURY:
We need to breach those carriers

01:30:54.900 --> 01:30:57.539
and replace their targeting
blades with our own.

01:30:57.540 --> 01:30:58.739
HILL: One or two won't cut it.

01:30:58.740 --> 01:31:01.459
We need to link all three
carriers for this to work,

01:31:01.460 --> 01:31:05.019
because if even one of those
ships remains operational,

01:31:05.020 --> 01:31:07.019
a whole lot of people
are gonna die.

01:31:07.020 --> 01:31:10.499
We have to assume everyone
aboard those carriers is HYDRA.

01:31:10.500 --> 01:31:12.819
We have to get past them,
insert these server blades.

01:31:12.820 --> 01:31:16.099
And maybe, just maybe we
can salvage what's left...

01:31:16.100 --> 01:31:17.299
ROGERS:
We're not salvaging anything.

01:31:17.300 --> 01:31:18.779
We're not just taking
down the carriers, Nick.

01:31:18.780 --> 01:31:19.899
We're taking down S.H.I.E.L.D.

01:31:19.900 --> 01:31:21.379
S.H.I.E.L.D. had nothing
to do with this.

01:31:21.380 --> 01:31:23.699
You gave me this mission.
This is how it ends.

01:31:23.700 --> 01:31:26.019
S.H.I.E.L.D.'s been compromised.
You said so yourself.

01:31:26.020 --> 01:31:27.899
HYDRA grew right under your
nose and nobody noticed.

01:31:27.900 --> 01:31:31.419
Why do you think we're meeting
in this cave? I noticed.

01:31:31.420 --> 01:31:33.504
How many paid the
price before you did?

01:31:36.140 --> 01:31:38.099
Look, I didn't know about Barnes.

01:31:38.100 --> 01:31:39.980
ROGERS: Even if you had,
would you have told me?

01:31:40.220 --> 01:31:43.139
Or would you have
compartmentalised that, too?

01:31:43.140 --> 01:31:46.139
S.H.I.E.L.D., HYDRA,

01:31:46.140 --> 01:31:47.826
it all goes.

01:31:47.940 --> 01:31:49.546
HILL: He's right.

01:31:54.940 --> 01:31:56.179
WILSON: Don't look at me.

01:31:56.180 --> 01:31:58.469
I do what he does, just slower.

01:32:01.780 --> 01:32:03.830
Well...

01:32:05.820 --> 01:32:07.745
(SIGHS)

01:32:09.700 --> 01:32:12.501
It looks like you're giving
the orders now, Captain.

01:32:23.740 --> 01:32:25.299
<i>BUCKY: We looked for you, after.</i>

01:32:25.300 --> 01:32:26.499
(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)

01:32:26.500 --> 01:32:28.699
<i>My folks wanted to give you
a ride to the cemetery.</i>

01:32:28.700 --> 01:32:32.707
I know, I'm sorry. I just
kind of wanted to be alone.

01:32:33.420 --> 01:32:35.231
How was it?

01:32:35.300 --> 01:32:37.190
It was okay.

01:32:37.220 --> 01:32:39.543
She's next to Dad.

01:32:40.620 --> 01:32:42.299
I was gonna ask...

01:32:42.300 --> 01:32:44.190
I know what you're gonna
say, Buck. I just...

01:32:44.940 --> 01:32:46.659
BUCKY: We can put the couch
cushions on the floor

01:32:46.660 --> 01:32:48.550
like when we were kids.

01:32:48.820 --> 01:32:51.700
It'll be fun. All you got
to do is shine my shoes,

01:32:51.740 --> 01:32:53.824
maybe take out the trash.

01:32:58.460 --> 01:33:00.271
Come on.

01:33:02.900 --> 01:33:06.747
Thank you, Buck, but I
can get by on my own.

01:33:07.140 --> 01:33:11.306
The thing is, you don't have to.

01:33:14.260 --> 01:33:16.264
I'm with you to the
end of the line, pal.

01:33:16.980 --> 01:33:18.586
(SIGHS)

01:33:19.180 --> 01:33:20.579
He's gonna be there, you know.

01:33:20.580 --> 01:33:22.027
I know.

01:33:22.500 --> 01:33:26.268
Look, whoever he used to
be and the guy he is now,

01:33:26.500 --> 01:33:28.899
I don't think he's
the kind you save.

01:33:28.900 --> 01:33:30.745
He's the kind you stop.

01:33:33.020 --> 01:33:34.939
I don't know if I can do that.

01:33:34.940 --> 01:33:37.099
Well, he might not
give you a choice.

01:33:37.100 --> 01:33:38.990
He doesn't know you.

01:33:39.300 --> 01:33:40.747
He will.

01:33:43.100 --> 01:33:44.786
Gear up. It's time.

01:33:47.020 --> 01:33:48.379
You gonna wear that?

01:33:48.380 --> 01:33:52.148
No. If you're gonna fight a
war, you got to wear a uniform.

01:33:59.660 --> 01:34:01.505
Oh, man.

01:34:01.900 --> 01:34:04.382
I am so fired.

01:34:28.860 --> 01:34:31.501
<i>MAN ON PA:
We are in final launch sequence.</i>

01:34:32.740 --> 01:34:35.063
We are go on guidance.

01:34:36.580 --> 01:34:39.108
<i>WOMAN ON PA:
All personnel to launch stations.</i>

01:34:39.460 --> 01:34:40.859
PIERCE: And how was your flight?

01:34:40.860 --> 01:34:41.979
HAWLEY: Lovely.

01:34:41.980 --> 01:34:44.579
The ride from the airport, less so.

01:34:44.580 --> 01:34:47.259
Sadly, S.H.I.E.L.D. can't
control everything.

01:34:47.260 --> 01:34:49.583
Including Captain America.

01:34:52.620 --> 01:34:55.379
This facility is
biometrically controlled.

01:34:55.380 --> 01:34:58.670
And these will give you
unrestricted access.

01:35:02.220 --> 01:35:03.619
TECH 1: I've been parking
there for two months.

01:35:03.620 --> 01:35:05.419
- TECH 2: But it's his spot.
- TECH 1: So where's he been?

01:35:05.420 --> 01:35:06.739
TECH 2: I think Afghanistan.

01:35:06.740 --> 01:35:08.939
Negative DT Six.
The pattern is full.

01:35:08.940 --> 01:35:10.339
Well, he could've said something.

01:35:10.340 --> 01:35:11.899
- (HIGH-PITCHED FEEDBACK)
- ALL: Ahh!

01:35:11.900 --> 01:35:13.631
Must be the dish.

01:35:15.020 --> 01:35:17.024
I'll check it out.

01:35:17.460 --> 01:35:20.864
<i>MAN ON PA: Triskelion command request
we clear the area for launch.</i>

01:35:24.140 --> 01:35:25.179
Excuse us.

01:35:25.180 --> 01:35:28.026
<i>PIERCE: I know the road
hasn't exactly been smooth,</i>

01:35:28.140 --> 01:35:31.862
and some of you would have gladly
kicked me out of the car along the way.

01:35:33.740 --> 01:35:35.107
Finally, we're here.

01:35:35.420 --> 01:35:37.743
And the world should be grateful.

01:35:38.300 --> 01:35:40.219
<i>ROGERS ON PA:
Attention all S.H.I.E.L.D. agents,</i>

01:35:40.220 --> 01:35:42.384
<i>this is Steve Rogers.</i>

01:35:43.780 --> 01:35:46.387
<i>You've heard a lot about
me over the last few days.</i>

01:35:47.020 --> 01:35:49.707
<i>Some of you were even
ordered to hunt me down.</i>

01:35:49.980 --> 01:35:53.270
But I think it's time
you know the truth.

01:35:56.020 --> 01:35:58.379
S.H.I.E.L.D. is not
what we thought it was.

01:35:58.380 --> 01:36:00.509
It's been taken over by HYDRA.

01:36:01.220 --> 01:36:03.304
<i>Alexander Pierce is their leader.</i>

01:36:07.020 --> 01:36:09.539
<i>The S.T.R.I.K.E. and Insight
crew are HYDRA as well.</i>

01:36:09.540 --> 01:36:10.987
<i>I don't know how many more,</i>

01:36:11.900 --> 01:36:13.301
but I know they're in the building.

01:36:14.700 --> 01:36:16.989
<i>They could be standing
right next to you.</i>

01:36:18.140 --> 01:36:20.224
<i>They almost have what they want.</i>

01:36:20.620 --> 01:36:23.102
<i>Absolute control.</i>

01:36:23.180 --> 01:36:24.945
They shot Nick Fury.

01:36:25.660 --> 01:36:27.186
<i>And it won't end there.</i>

01:36:27.340 --> 01:36:29.699
If you launch those
helicarriers today,

01:36:29.700 --> 01:36:32.102
<i>HYDRA will be able to kill
anyone that stands in their way.</i>

01:36:34.980 --> 01:36:36.791
<i>Unless we stop them.</i>

01:36:40.380 --> 01:36:41.906
<i>I know I'm asking a lot.</i>

01:36:43.420 --> 01:36:46.983
<i>But the price of freedom is high.
It always has been.</i>

01:36:47.340 --> 01:36:49.629
And it's a price I'm
willing to pay.

01:36:51.580 --> 01:36:54.790
And if I'm the only
one, then so be it.

01:36:56.060 --> 01:36:58.224
But I'm Willing to bet I'm not.

01:37:02.580 --> 01:37:06.268
Did you write that down first,
or was it off the top of your head?

01:37:06.380 --> 01:37:08.384
You smug son of a bitch.

01:37:12.060 --> 01:37:13.541
Arrest him.

01:37:15.980 --> 01:37:18.030
I guess I've got the floor.

01:37:24.500 --> 01:37:27.824
Preempt the launch sequence.
Send those ships up now.

01:37:31.820 --> 01:37:33.379
Is there a problem?

01:37:33.380 --> 01:37:34.781
Um...

01:37:38.340 --> 01:37:39.619
Is there a problem?

01:37:39.620 --> 01:37:41.101
I'm sorry, sir.

01:37:41.580 --> 01:37:43.664
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:37:49.420 --> 01:37:52.027
I'm not gonna launch those ships.

01:37:54.340 --> 01:37:55.819
Captain's orders.

01:37:55.820 --> 01:37:57.459
Move away from your station.

01:37:57.460 --> 01:37:58.659
Like he said...

01:37:58.660 --> 01:37:59.779
Hold it right there.

01:37:59.780 --> 01:38:01.299
Put the gun down!

01:38:01.300 --> 01:38:02.701
Captain's orders.

01:38:04.700 --> 01:38:06.545
You picked the wrong side, Agent.

01:38:07.980 --> 01:38:09.984
Depends on where you're standing.

01:38:21.420 --> 01:38:23.231
- (GUN CLATTERS)
- (GASPS)

01:38:23.700 --> 01:38:25.545
- (GROANS)
- (PEOPLE GASP)

01:38:26.620 --> 01:38:29.068
(ALL GRUNTING)

01:38:53.980 --> 01:38:55.619
S.H.I.E.L.D. AGENT:
Close the bay door!

01:38:55.620 --> 01:38:57.260
Close the bay door now!

01:38:57.340 --> 01:38:58.707
Close the bay door!

01:39:18.180 --> 01:39:19.786
They're initiating launch.

01:39:39.580 --> 01:39:42.379
Hey, Cap, how do we know the
good guys from the bad guys?

01:39:42.380 --> 01:39:44.270
If they're shooting
at you, they're bad.

01:40:01.380 --> 01:40:03.111
(GROANING)

01:40:17.220 --> 01:40:18.419
Hey, Cap,

01:40:18.420 --> 01:40:20.499
I found those bad guys
you were talking about.

01:40:20.500 --> 01:40:21.901
You Okay?

01:40:23.660 --> 01:40:25.585
I'm not dead yet.

01:40:32.140 --> 01:40:34.304
PIERCE: Let me ask you a question.

01:40:36.420 --> 01:40:39.949
What if Pakistan marched
into Mumbai tomorrow

01:40:40.820 --> 01:40:43.179
and you knew that they were
going to drag your daughters

01:40:43.180 --> 01:40:46.345
into a soccer stadium
for execution,

01:40:48.380 --> 01:40:51.939
and you could just stop it,
with a flick of the switch.

01:40:51.940 --> 01:40:53.299
Wouldn't you?

01:40:53.300 --> 01:40:55.350
Wouldn't you all?

01:40:56.820 --> 01:40:58.710
Not if it was your switch.

01:40:59.260 --> 01:41:01.264
(GLASS SHATTERS)

01:41:01.500 --> 01:41:03.061
(CHUCKLES)

01:41:07.740 --> 01:41:09.630
(ALL GRUNTING)

01:41:22.820 --> 01:41:24.426
I'm sorry.

01:41:30.460 --> 01:41:32.430
Did I step on your moment?

01:41:33.580 --> 01:41:36.267
Satellites in range at 3,000 feet.

01:41:36.820 --> 01:41:38.219
Falcon, status?

01:41:38.220 --> 01:41:39.781
Engaging.

01:42:03.500 --> 01:42:05.186
All right, Cap. I'm in.

01:42:07.180 --> 01:42:08.627
Oh, shit.

01:42:32.060 --> 01:42:33.985
(ALL GRUNTING)

01:42:38.740 --> 01:42:40.585
<i>HILL: Eight minutes, Cap.</i>

01:42:40.700 --> 01:42:42.465
Working on it.

01:42:50.420 --> 01:42:51.539
What are you doing?

01:42:51.540 --> 01:42:53.219
She's disabling security protocols

01:42:53.220 --> 01:42:55.179
and dumping all the secrets
onto the Internet.

01:42:55.180 --> 01:42:57.150
- Including HYDRA'S.
- And S.H.I.E.L.D.'s.

01:42:58.100 --> 01:42:59.419
If you do this,

01:42:59.420 --> 01:43:01.504
none of your past is
gonna remain hidden.

01:43:04.180 --> 01:43:06.899
Are you sure you're ready
for the world to see you

01:43:06.900 --> 01:43:08.825
as you really are?

01:43:09.180 --> 01:43:11.025
Are you?

01:43:26.860 --> 01:43:28.307
Alpha lock.

01:43:30.020 --> 01:43:31.499
Falcon, where are you now?

01:43:31.500 --> 01:43:32.822
I had to take a detour.

01:43:59.860 --> 01:44:01.307
(GRUNTS)

01:44:03.340 --> 01:44:04.741
Whoo!

01:44:05.020 --> 01:44:07.024
Oh, yeah!

01:44:12.620 --> 01:44:14.067
I'm in.

01:44:17.300 --> 01:44:19.543
Bravo lock.

01:44:20.940 --> 01:44:22.626
Two down, one to go.

01:44:24.500 --> 01:44:26.425
LEAD PILOT:
All S.H.I.E.L.D. pilots, scramble.

01:44:26.900 --> 01:44:29.906
We're the only air support
Captain Rogers has got.

01:44:42.620 --> 01:44:44.260
(GROANS)

01:45:11.980 --> 01:45:14.859
Disabling the encryption
is an executive order.

01:45:14.860 --> 01:45:16.739
It takes two Alpha Level members.

01:45:16.740 --> 01:45:18.779
Don't worry. Company's coming.

01:45:18.780 --> 01:45:20.625
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

01:45:42.300 --> 01:45:43.826
Did you get my flowers?

01:45:46.140 --> 01:45:48.224
- PIERCE: I'm glad you're here, Nick.
- Really?

01:45:49.780 --> 01:45:51.859
Because I thought
you had me killed.

01:45:51.860 --> 01:45:53.705
You know how the game works.

01:45:54.380 --> 01:45:56.179
So why make me head
of S.H.I.E.L.D.?

01:45:56.180 --> 01:45:57.659
Because you were the best,

01:45:57.660 --> 01:45:59.419
and the most ruthless
person I ever met.

01:45:59.420 --> 01:46:02.061
I did what I did to protect people.

01:46:02.580 --> 01:46:04.948
Our enemies are your enemies, Nick.

01:46:05.460 --> 01:46:08.181
Disorder. War.

01:46:08.780 --> 01:46:11.299
It's just a matter of time before
a dirty bomb goes off in Moscow,

01:46:11.300 --> 01:46:13.862
or an EMP fries Chicago.

01:46:15.020 --> 01:46:16.619
Diplomacy?

01:46:16.620 --> 01:46:19.341
A holding action, Nick. A band-aid.

01:46:19.860 --> 01:46:23.184
And you know where I
learned that. Bogota.

01:46:24.540 --> 01:46:27.671
You didn't ask. You just
did what had to be done.

01:46:28.460 --> 01:46:33.184
I can bring order to the lives
of seven billion people

01:46:33.460 --> 01:46:35.510
by sacrificing 20 million.

01:46:36.660 --> 01:46:38.819
It's the next step, Nick.

01:46:38.820 --> 01:46:40.139
If you have the courage to take it.

01:46:40.140 --> 01:46:42.622
No. I have the courage not to.

01:46:46.740 --> 01:46:48.699
<i>S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
Retinal scanner active.</i>

01:46:48.700 --> 01:46:50.099
(CHUCKLES)

01:46:50.100 --> 01:46:52.659
You don't think we've wiped
your clearance from the system?

01:46:52.660 --> 01:46:54.819
I know you erased my password.

01:46:54.820 --> 01:46:57.143
Probably deleted my retinal scan.

01:46:57.300 --> 01:47:00.544
But if you want to stay
ahead of me, Mr Secretary,

01:47:04.140 --> 01:47:07.510
you need to keep both eyes open.

01:47:11.500 --> 01:47:13.425
<i>COMPUTER: Alpha level confirmed.</i>

01:47:13.500 --> 01:47:15.499
<i>Encryption code accepted.</i>

01:47:15.500 --> 01:47:17.059
<i>Safeguards removed.</i>

01:47:17.060 --> 01:47:20.464
Charlie carrier is 45
degrees off the port bow.

01:47:23.740 --> 01:47:25.585
(HYDRA SOLDIERS GROANING)

01:47:25.780 --> 01:47:27.019
Six minutes.

01:47:27.020 --> 01:47:29.900
Hey, Sam, gonna need a ride.

01:47:30.380 --> 01:47:32.430
Roger. Let me know
when you're ready.

01:47:34.660 --> 01:47:36.266
I just did!

01:47:44.220 --> 01:47:46.190
(GROANS)

01:47:53.620 --> 01:47:55.739
You know, you're a lot
heavier than you look.

01:47:55.740 --> 01:47:57.266
I had a big breakfast.

01:47:59.460 --> 01:48:01.191
Steve!

01:48:02.620 --> 01:48:04.431
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:48:27.180 --> 01:48:28.820
(YELLING)

01:48:31.260 --> 01:48:33.025
<i>WILSON:
Cap! Cap, come in. Are you okay?</i>

01:48:33.220 --> 01:48:34.906
Yeah, I'm here.

01:48:35.060 --> 01:48:36.507
I'm still on the helicarrier.

01:48:37.140 --> 01:48:39.190
- Where are you?
- I'm grounded.

01:48:39.380 --> 01:48:42.147
The suit's down. Sorry, Cap.

01:48:42.540 --> 01:48:44.829
Don't worry. I got it.

01:48:45.340 --> 01:48:46.419
(ALARM BLARING)

01:48:46.420 --> 01:48:48.139
<i>WOMAN: (ON PA)
Emergency evacuation alert.</i>

01:48:48.140 --> 01:48:51.510
<i>All personnel, proceed to
designated safety zones.</i>

01:48:52.700 --> 01:48:54.659
S.H.I.E.L.D. AGENT: All S.H.I.E.L.D.
agents regroup at Rally Point Delta.

01:48:54.660 --> 01:48:57.188
- (YELLS)
- (ALL GRUNTING)

01:49:00.300 --> 01:49:02.739
<i>DISPATCH: (ON RADIO)
Sir, the Council's been breached.</i>

01:49:02.740 --> 01:49:05.339
- Repeat, Dispatch.
<i>- Black Widow's up there.</i>

01:49:05.340 --> 01:49:07.071
Headed up.

01:49:08.860 --> 01:49:10.259
- Falcon?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

01:49:10.260 --> 01:49:11.299
Rumlow's headed for the Council.

01:49:11.300 --> 01:49:12.701
I'm on it.

01:49:23.900 --> 01:49:25.347
People are gonna die, Buck.

01:49:27.060 --> 01:49:28.950
I can't let that happen.

01:49:36.980 --> 01:49:38.745
Please don't make me do this.

01:49:56.980 --> 01:49:59.269
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:50:48.540 --> 01:50:49.987
Done.

01:50:50.580 --> 01:50:51.981
And it's trending.

01:50:56.100 --> 01:50:57.865
(GROANING)

01:50:59.220 --> 01:51:01.139
Unless you want a two-inch
hole in your sternum,

01:51:01.140 --> 01:51:02.666
I'd put that gun down.

01:51:04.940 --> 01:51:07.308
That was armed the
moment you pinned it on.

01:51:22.260 --> 01:51:23.866
(GROANS)

01:51:25.780 --> 01:51:27.181
Ahhh!

01:51:40.740 --> 01:51:42.221
Drop it!

01:51:42.460 --> 01:51:43.619
Drop it!

01:51:43.620 --> 01:51:45.306
(SCREAMS)

01:52:03.980 --> 01:52:07.623
I'm on 41, headed toward
the southwest stairwell.

01:52:09.820 --> 01:52:12.541
(GROANING)

01:52:13.940 --> 01:52:15.944
This is gonna hurt.

01:52:16.820 --> 01:52:20.099
There are no prisoners
with HYDRA. Just order.

01:52:20.100 --> 01:52:22.741
And order only comes through pain.

01:52:23.740 --> 01:52:26.507
- You ready for yours?
- Man, shut the hell up.

01:52:27.900 --> 01:52:29.339
Lieutenant, how much longer?

01:52:29.340 --> 01:52:31.499
<i>CHARLIE XO: (ON RADIO)
65 seconds to satellite link.</i>

01:52:31.500 --> 01:52:34.904
Targeting grid engaged.
Lowering weapons array now.

01:52:38.500 --> 01:52:39.981
One minute.

01:52:43.660 --> 01:52:45.744
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GROANS)

01:52:59.500 --> 01:53:01.425
<i>HILL: (ON RADIO) 30 seconds, Cap.</i>

01:53:02.660 --> 01:53:04.585
Stand by. (GROANS)

01:53:06.860 --> 01:53:08.910
Charlie... (GROANS)

01:53:11.220 --> 01:53:13.031
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:53:17.780 --> 01:53:20.061
<i>CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH: (ON RADIO)
We've reached 3,000 feet.</i>

01:53:20.100 --> 01:53:21.501
Sat link coming online now.

01:53:23.620 --> 01:53:25.101
Deploy algorithm.

01:53:26.380 --> 01:53:27.981
CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH:
Algorithm deployed.

01:53:28.780 --> 01:53:30.625
<i>PIERCE: (ON RADIO)
We are go to target.</i>

01:53:49.300 --> 01:53:51.059
<i>CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH:
Target saturation reached.</i>

01:53:51.060 --> 01:53:52.139
All targets assigned.

01:53:52.140 --> 01:53:53.587
Fire when ready.

01:53:55.660 --> 01:53:57.019
Firing in...

01:53:57.020 --> 01:53:58.379
<i>Three,</i>

01:53:58.380 --> 01:53:59.459
two...

01:53:59.460 --> 01:54:00.579
(GRUNTS)

01:54:00.580 --> 01:54:02.311
One.

01:54:04.580 --> 01:54:06.027
(PANTS) Charlie lock.

01:54:06.100 --> 01:54:07.501
Where are the targets?

01:54:08.580 --> 01:54:09.981
Where are the targets?

01:54:10.220 --> 01:54:11.826
Okay, Cap, get out of there.

01:54:28.860 --> 01:54:30.261
Fire now.

01:54:30.940 --> 01:54:32.580
- But, Steve...
- Do it!

01:54:32.940 --> 01:54:34.501
<i>Do it now!</i>

01:54:57.340 --> 01:54:59.151
(WINTER SOLDIER SCREAMING)

01:55:04.660 --> 01:55:05.819
What a waste.

01:55:05.820 --> 01:55:09.219
ROMANOFF: So, you still on the
fence about Rogers' chances?

01:55:09.220 --> 01:55:12.703
Time to go, Councilwoman.
This way. Come on.

01:55:12.780 --> 01:55:14.499
You're going to fly me out of here.

01:55:14.500 --> 01:55:17.859
You know, there was a time I
would've taken a bullet for you.

01:55:17.860 --> 01:55:19.339
You already did.

01:55:19.340 --> 01:55:21.708
- You will again, when it's useful.
- (GROANING)

01:55:34.620 --> 01:55:36.181
Romanoff.

01:55:36.500 --> 01:55:37.981
Natasha.

01:55:39.660 --> 01:55:41.824
Natasha! Come on!

01:55:45.820 --> 01:55:47.460
Ow.

01:55:48.500 --> 01:55:50.425
Those really do sting.

01:56:23.060 --> 01:56:24.871
(WEAKLY) Hail HYDRA.

01:56:57.340 --> 01:56:59.151
(GRUNTING)

01:57:12.700 --> 01:57:14.625
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:57:15.820 --> 01:57:17.460
(GROANS)

01:57:19.940 --> 01:57:21.830
You're out of your depth, kid.

01:57:25.140 --> 01:57:27.030
Son of a bitch!

01:57:38.780 --> 01:57:40.750
Please tell me you got
that chopper in the air!

01:57:41.140 --> 01:57:42.701
<i>ROMANOFF: (ON RADIO)
Sam, where are you?</i>

01:57:43.140 --> 01:57:45.179
41 st floor! Northwest corner!

01:57:45.180 --> 01:57:46.939
We're on it! Stay where you are!

01:57:46.940 --> 01:57:48.421
Not an option!

01:58:02.820 --> 01:58:05.339
41st floor! 41st!

01:58:05.340 --> 01:58:09.062
It's not like they put the floor numbers
on the outside of the building.

01:58:10.060 --> 01:58:12.940
Hill! Where's Steve? You
got a location on Rogers?

01:58:16.540 --> 01:58:18.669
(STRAINING)

01:58:20.020 --> 01:58:21.660
(GRUNTS)

01:58:29.020 --> 01:58:30.501
You know me.

01:58:31.860 --> 01:58:33.591
No, I don't!

01:58:40.500 --> 01:58:42.140
(PANTING)

01:58:42.700 --> 01:58:44.431
Bucky.

01:58:45.540 --> 01:58:47.385
You've known me your whole life.

01:58:54.540 --> 01:58:58.659
Your name is James Buchanan Barnes.

01:58:58.660 --> 01:59:00.300
Shut up!

01:59:08.620 --> 01:59:10.465
I'm not gonna fight you.

01:59:14.060 --> 01:59:15.791
You're my friend.

01:59:19.420 --> 01:59:21.310
- (ROARS)
- (GRUNTS)

01:59:22.420 --> 01:59:23.899
You're my mission.

01:59:23.900 --> 01:59:25.665
(GRUNTING)

01:59:26.060 --> 01:59:28.462
You're my mission!

01:59:31.420 --> 01:59:32.821
Then finish it.

01:59:35.900 --> 01:59:38.507
Because I'm with you to
the end of the line.

02:01:26.220 --> 02:01:28.384
(R&B MUSIC PLAYING)

02:01:49.780 --> 02:01:51.511
On your left.

02:01:56.740 --> 02:01:59.188
(R&B MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING)

02:02:16.980 --> 02:02:19.382
(INAUDIBLE)

02:02:42.100 --> 02:02:44.699
<i>FEMALE BAILIFF: Do you solemnly swear
to tell the truth, the whole truth,</i>

02:02:44.700 --> 02:02:45.979
<i>and nothing but the truth?</i>

02:02:45.980 --> 02:02:47.825
<i>ROMANOFF: I do.</i>

02:02:49.420 --> 02:02:51.299
<i>COMMITTEE MEMBER: Why haven't
we yet heard from Captain Rogers?</i>

02:02:51.300 --> 02:02:53.065
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

02:02:53.820 --> 02:02:55.939
I don't know what there
is left for him to say.

02:02:55.940 --> 02:02:57.979
I think the wreck in the
middle of the Potomac

02:02:57.980 --> 02:02:59.379
made his point fairly eloquently.

02:02:59.380 --> 02:03:00.539
COMMITTEE MEMBER:
Well, he could explain how

02:03:00.540 --> 02:03:03.299
this country is expected to
maintain its national security

02:03:03.300 --> 02:03:07.819
now that he and you have laid waste
to our intelligence apparatus.

02:03:07.820 --> 02:03:09.979
HYDRA was selling you
lies, not intelligence.

02:03:09.980 --> 02:03:13.059
Many of which you seemed to have
had a personal hand in telling.

02:03:13.060 --> 02:03:14.459
Agent, you should know

02:03:14.460 --> 02:03:16.339
that there are some
on this committee

02:03:16.340 --> 02:03:18.659
who feel, given your
service record,

02:03:18.660 --> 02:03:20.789
both for this country
and against it,

02:03:21.140 --> 02:03:23.099
that you belong in a penitentiary.

02:03:23.100 --> 02:03:25.468
Not mouthing off on Capitol Hill.

02:03:26.980 --> 02:03:28.984
You're not going to
put me in a prison.

02:03:29.580 --> 02:03:33.905
You're not going to put any of
us in a prison. You know why?

02:03:34.940 --> 02:03:36.619
Do enlighten us.

02:03:36.620 --> 02:03:38.351
Because you need us.

02:03:39.060 --> 02:03:41.539
<i>Yes, the world is a
vulnerable place,</i>

02:03:41.540 --> 02:03:44.102
<i>and yes, we help make it that way.</i>

02:03:44.260 --> 02:03:47.425
<i>But we're also the ones best
qualified to defend it.</i>

02:03:48.660 --> 02:03:51.028
So, if you want to
arrest me, arrest me.

02:03:51.660 --> 02:03:53.744
You'll know where to find me.

02:04:28.820 --> 02:04:32.064
So, you've experienced
this sort of thing before.

02:04:32.180 --> 02:04:34.105
You get used to it.

02:04:36.420 --> 02:04:38.819
We've been data
mining HYDRA'S files.

02:04:38.820 --> 02:04:41.348
Looks like a lot of rats
didn't go down with the ship.

02:04:42.500 --> 02:04:44.265
I'm headed to Europe tonight.

02:04:44.820 --> 02:04:46.460
Wanted to ask if you'd come.

02:04:47.220 --> 02:04:49.270
There's something I
got to do first.

02:04:49.780 --> 02:04:52.706
How about you, Wilson? Could
use a man with your abilities.

02:04:53.380 --> 02:04:55.464
I'm more of a soldier than a spy.

02:04:56.180 --> 02:04:58.344
All right, then.

02:05:02.580 --> 02:05:07.190
Anybody asks for me, tell them
they can find me, right here.

02:05:08.580 --> 02:05:10.379
You should be honoured. That's
about as close as he gets

02:05:10.380 --> 02:05:12.430
to saying thank you.

02:05:13.180 --> 02:05:14.661
Not going with him?

02:05:14.740 --> 02:05:16.219
No.

02:05:16.220 --> 02:05:18.622
- Not staying here.
- Nah.

02:05:19.060 --> 02:05:21.419
I blew all my covers. I got
to go figure out a new one.

02:05:21.420 --> 02:05:22.821
That might take a while.

02:05:22.940 --> 02:05:24.944
I'm counting on it.

02:05:26.780 --> 02:05:28.259
That thing you asked for,

02:05:28.260 --> 02:05:30.981
I called in a few
favours from Kiev.

02:05:33.540 --> 02:05:36.671
Will you do me a favour?
Call that nurse.

02:05:36.700 --> 02:05:38.099
She's not a nurse.

02:05:38.100 --> 02:05:40.343
And you're not a
S.H.I.E.L.D. agent.

02:05:40.860 --> 02:05:43.342
- What was her name again?
- Sharon.

02:05:43.700 --> 02:05:45.101
She's nice.

02:05:57.180 --> 02:05:59.344
Be careful, Steve.

02:05:59.780 --> 02:06:01.909
You might not want to
pull on that thread.

02:06:13.060 --> 02:06:15.219
You're going after him.

02:06:15.220 --> 02:06:16.659
You don't have to come with me.

02:06:16.660 --> 02:06:18.141
I know.

02:06:19.700 --> 02:06:21.261
When do we start?

02:08:20.260 --> 02:08:24.301
It's over. Fury has released
everything to the public.

02:08:24.620 --> 02:08:26.351
Everything he knows about.

02:08:26.540 --> 02:08:28.579
<i>Herr</i> Strucker, if they get
word of our work here,

02:08:28.580 --> 02:08:30.579
if they find out we serve HYDRA...

02:08:30.580 --> 02:08:32.709
HYDRA, S.H.I.E.L.D.

02:08:33.300 --> 02:08:36.544
Two sides of a coin that's
no longer currency.

02:08:39.980 --> 02:08:41.870
What we have

02:08:43.500 --> 02:08:46.551
is worth more than any
of them ever knew.

02:08:48.780 --> 02:08:52.866
We've only scratched the
surface and already,

02:08:55.260 --> 02:08:59.506
there are other facilities doing
HYDRA'S good work around the world.

02:09:00.260 --> 02:09:03.899
We'll feed them to Captain America
and his colourful friends,

02:09:03.900 --> 02:09:05.939
and keep them off our scent.

02:09:05.940 --> 02:09:08.419
What about the volunteers?

02:09:08.420 --> 02:09:10.179
The dead will be buried so deep

02:09:10.180 --> 02:09:12.708
their own ghosts won't
be able to find them.

02:09:14.380 --> 02:09:16.020
And the survivors?

02:09:17.740 --> 02:09:19.665
The twins.

02:09:22.820 --> 02:09:26.349
Sooner or later,
they will meet the twins.

02:09:28.140 --> 02:09:30.259
It's not a world of spies any more.

02:09:30.260 --> 02:09:32.628
Not even a world of heroes.

02:09:33.220 --> 02:09:36.351
This is the age of
miracles, Doctor.

02:09:37.820 --> 02:09:40.507
There's nothing more horrifying

02:09:40.940 --> 02:09:42.466
than a miracle.
